WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:38.038 --> 00:00:41.124
1879. The Civil War is over.

3
00:00:41.208 --> 00:00:45.628
and the resulting economic explosion
spurs the great migration west.

4
00:00:45.754 --> 00:00:50.174
Farmers. ranchers. prospectors.
killers and thieves seek their fortunes.

5
00:00:51.260 --> 00:00:54.178
Cattle drovers turn cow towns
into armed camps

6
00:00:54.263 --> 00:00:59.726
with murder rates higher than those of
modern-day New York or Los Angeles.

7
00:00:59.810 --> 00:01:03.146
Out of this chaos comes
legendary lawman Wyatt Earp.

8
00:01:03.272 --> 00:01:07.608
retiring his badge and gun to start
a peaceful life with his family.

9
00:01:07.693 --> 00:01:10.361
Earp's friend. John "Doc" Holliday.

10
00:01:10.487 --> 00:01:12.697
a Southern gentleman
turned gunman and gambler.

11
00:01:12.781 --> 00:01:17.910
also travels west. hoping the dry
climate will relieve his tuberculosis.

12
00:01:17.995 --> 00:01:20.288
Silver is discovered in Arizona.

13
00:01:20.372 --> 00:01:23.082
Tombstone becomes
queen of the boomtowns.

14
00:01:23.167 --> 00:01:27.128
where the latest Paris fashions
are sold from the backs of wagons.

15
00:01:27.212 --> 00:01:29.505
Attracted to this atmosphere of greed.

16
00:01:29.590 --> 00:01:32.967
over 100 exiled Texas outlaws
band together

17
00:01:33.051 --> 00:01:37.346
to form the ruthless gang recognized
by the red sashes they wear.

18
00:01:37.931 --> 00:01:42.101
They emerge as the earliest example
of organized crime in America.

19
00:01:42.478 --> 00:01:45.188
They call themselves the Cowboys.

20
00:03:20.242 --> 00:03:22.285
Y'all killed two Cowboys.

21
00:03:54.234 --> 00:03:55.735
Shoot.

22
00:03:57.905 --> 00:03:59.655
Looks like we win.

23
00:04:13.170 --> 00:04:15.671
Mexican police. huh?

24
00:04:20.218 --> 00:04:22.470
Tell him to get on his knees.

25
00:04:32.481 --> 00:04:35.816
He will not kneel. patrón.
He is very proud.

26
00:04:36.693 --> 00:04:39.445
Hey. somebody get
this spic on his knees.

27
00:04:42.991 --> 00:04:44.742
Good shot. Billy.

28
00:04:51.792 --> 00:04:54.126
They call me Curly Bill Brocius.

29
00:04:55.295 --> 00:04:59.632
I'm what you might call
the Founder of the Feast.

30
00:05:00.550 --> 00:05:04.720
So next time we come.
you'd better step aside.

31
00:05:07.391 --> 00:05:09.517
I ain't kiddin' neither.

32
00:05:19.611 --> 00:05:24.073
Patrón. he say.
someone will come to revenge for him.

33
00:05:24.658 --> 00:05:27.576
Something like a sick horse
who comes to sit with him.

34
00:05:27.661 --> 00:05:29.412
He talk crazy.

35
00:05:30.455 --> 00:05:33.666
That's not what he said.
ya ignorant wretch.

36
00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:36.627
Your Spanish is worse
than your English.

37
00:05:39.006 --> 00:05:41.090
You go to hell!

38
00:05:41.758 --> 00:05:43.175
You first.

39
00:06:09.327 --> 00:06:12.121
-Hell. let's eat. boys.
-Tamales are good. huh?

40
00:06:12.247 --> 00:06:14.749
I guess they knew we were comin'.

41
00:06:37.314 --> 00:06:40.357
Hey. Johnny.
what'd that Mexican mean.

42
00:06:40.484 --> 00:06:43.110
"A sick horse is gonna get us"?

43
00:06:44.571 --> 00:06:46.697
He's quoting the Bible.

44
00:06:47.199 --> 00:06:48.699
Revelations.

45
00:06:50.368 --> 00:06:55.331
"Behold. a pale horse.
The man who sat on him was Death."

46
00:06:57.834 --> 00:07:00.169
"And Hell followed with him."

47
00:07:27.989 --> 00:07:29.240
Move!

48
00:07:31.827 --> 00:07:34.745
Come on! That's it! You move!

49
00:07:36.623 --> 00:07:38.374
Stupid mule!

50
00:07:39.584 --> 00:07:43.212
Come on! Come on. boy! Come on!

51
00:07:52.931 --> 00:07:54.723
Hurts. don't it?

52
00:07:55.600 --> 00:07:59.061
Now let go of that stud
and go on about your business.

53
00:08:11.700 --> 00:08:14.493
Mr. Earp. My name's Dake.

54
00:08:14.578 --> 00:08:17.204
Crawley Dake.
US Marshal for this territory.

55
00:08:17.289 --> 00:08:20.082
-Forget it. I'm retired.
-Excuse me?

56
00:08:20.584 --> 00:08:23.752
I said forget it.
I don't want the job. and that's final.

57
00:08:23.879 --> 00:08:27.214
-I don't think you understand.
-No. you don't understand. Marshal.

58
00:08:27.299 --> 00:08:31.302
I did my duty.
and now I'd like to get on with my life.

59
00:08:31.386 --> 00:08:32.678
I'm going to Tombstone.

60
00:08:32.762 --> 00:08:35.347
-I see. To strike it rich.
-Easy on the grain. Butch.

61
00:08:35.432 --> 00:08:37.183
-Here you go.
-Well. all right. that's fine.

62
00:08:37.267 --> 00:08:39.894
Tell you one thing. though.
Never saw a rich man

63
00:08:39.978 --> 00:08:43.022
who didn't wind up
with a guilty conscience.

64
00:08:43.106 --> 00:08:47.443
I already got a guilty conscience.
Might as well have the money too.

65
00:08:47.777 --> 00:08:49.278
Good day now.

66
00:08:52.657 --> 00:08:56.869
That's him. all right.
Boy. I'd know that sour face anywhere.

67
00:09:00.707 --> 00:09:02.791
Virgil! Morgan! My God!

68
00:09:08.882 --> 00:09:11.175
-Hey. boy! How are you. Morgan?
-Hi. Wyatt.

69
00:09:11.635 --> 00:09:13.928
-Well. how do we look?
-Great. both of ya.

70
00:09:14.012 --> 00:09:16.889
-Wyatt. you remember Allie.
-Good God. Well. he'd better.

71
00:09:16.973 --> 00:09:19.058
Allie girl.

72
00:09:19.142 --> 00:09:21.227
-And Louisa. Oh!
-Wyatt.

73
00:09:21.311 --> 00:09:24.438
You're so lovely. darlin'.
I'm at your feet. just at your feet.

74
00:09:24.522 --> 00:09:27.441
I guess it's only right.
Ma always said Morgan's the prettiest.

75
00:09:27.525 --> 00:09:31.487
-Yeah. but she doted on the frowner.
-That's right.

76
00:09:33.031 --> 00:09:34.031
-Wyatt.
-Mattie!

77
00:09:34.115 --> 00:09:37.576
Mattie. they're already here.
Folks. this is Celia Ann.

78
00:09:37.661 --> 00:09:40.079
-You can call her Mattie.
-Pleased to meet you. Mattie.

79
00:09:40.163 --> 00:09:42.581
It's nice to meet you.

80
00:09:42.666 --> 00:09:45.751
Well. Wyatt. I couldn't find a single
store that had laudanum anywhere.

81
00:09:45.835 --> 00:09:49.338
That's all right. honey.
I sure been dreamin' about this.

82
00:09:49.422 --> 00:09:52.925
God. since forever! Wait! Look here.

83
00:09:53.009 --> 00:09:55.511
Go on up. Look. Huh?

84
00:09:58.848 --> 00:10:01.350
-Hey. Wyatt.
-Don't talk. just...

85
00:10:01.434 --> 00:10:02.851
Yeah.

86
00:10:05.480 --> 00:10:07.147
Thank you for this. Wyatt.

87
00:10:07.232 --> 00:10:10.859
-It's all your doin'.
-We'll make our fortune. boys.

88
00:10:11.528 --> 00:10:13.195
Well. come on.

89
00:10:13.321 --> 00:10:15.698
Gracious. We could be sisters.

90
00:10:16.700 --> 00:10:19.118
Mighty fine.
I wonder where he found her.

91
00:10:19.202 --> 00:10:21.745
Same place we found ours. probably.

92
00:10:25.166 --> 00:10:28.127
Matter. hon? Did you say
you needed some laudanum?

93
00:10:28.211 --> 00:10:30.879
-Yes. I did. Yes.
-I have some right here.

94
00:10:31.006 --> 00:10:32.881
Oh. you're a lifesaver.

95
00:10:35.218 --> 00:10:37.094
Just be careful now. It's full of hop.

96
00:10:37.220 --> 00:10:39.930
Oh. don't worry.
I just get headaches sometimes.

97
00:10:40.056 --> 00:10:42.933
Hey. Virg. see anything of Doc
while you were in Prescott?

98
00:10:43.059 --> 00:10:45.936
Yeah. He had a streak
when we left. him and Kate.

99
00:10:46.021 --> 00:10:48.772
I miss Doc. I miss that old rip.

100
00:10:48.898 --> 00:10:52.234
-I don't.
-He makes me laugh.

101
00:10:59.200 --> 00:11:02.036
That's $500. Holliday.
Are you in or out?

102
00:11:11.504 --> 00:11:15.090
500. Must be a peach of a hand.

103
00:11:21.306 --> 00:11:23.599
Oh. thank you. darlin'.

104
00:11:23.725 --> 00:11:26.935
Kate! You're not wearing a bustle.

105
00:11:28.313 --> 00:11:29.521
How lewd.

106
00:11:29.606 --> 00:11:32.608
Come on. Holliday.
you in or out. goddamn it?

107
00:11:33.610 --> 00:11:37.488
Why. Ed Bailey. you look like
you're just about ready to burst.

108
00:11:37.614 --> 00:11:40.449
Come on! Come on. show!

109
00:11:41.826 --> 00:11:45.245
Well. I suppose I'm deranged. but I...

110
00:11:46.081 --> 00:11:48.832
I guess I'll just have to call.

111
00:11:48.917 --> 00:11:51.043
Cover your ears. darlin'.

112
00:11:53.880 --> 00:11:55.672
Isn't that a daisy?

113
00:11:56.466 --> 00:11:58.550
Why. you son of a bitch!

114
00:11:58.635 --> 00:12:00.594
Damn. Bailey. just settle down!

115
00:12:00.678 --> 00:12:04.556
Shut up! Take your money and get out.

116
00:12:05.141 --> 00:12:08.185
'cause I'm tired of
listenin' to your mouth.

117
00:12:08.269 --> 00:12:10.896
Why. Ed Bailey.

118
00:12:10.980 --> 00:12:12.564
are we cross?

119
00:12:14.567 --> 00:12:16.944
Them guns don't scare me.

120
00:12:17.028 --> 00:12:21.240
'Cause without them guns
you ain't nothin' but a skinny lunger.

121
00:12:21.324 --> 00:12:23.742
Ed. what an ugly thing to say.

122
00:12:25.370 --> 00:12:29.164
I abhor ugliness. Does this mean
we're not friends anymore?

123
00:12:29.916 --> 00:12:33.419
You know. Ed. if I thought
you weren't my friend.

124
00:12:34.587 --> 00:12:37.131
I just don't think I could bear it.

125
00:12:53.898 --> 00:12:56.942
There. Now we can be friends again.

126
00:13:09.122 --> 00:13:11.623
Touch that gun. I'll burn you down.

127
00:13:21.050 --> 00:13:23.844
I calculate that's the end of this town.

128
00:13:23.928 --> 00:13:28.056
I had a boy at the hotel pack us up.
The horse is outside.

129
00:13:28.725 --> 00:13:31.852
So that's why you're
not wearin' a bustle.

130
00:13:34.063 --> 00:13:37.357
My sweet. soft Hungarian devil.

131
00:13:42.113 --> 00:13:43.322
Well!

132
00:13:48.745 --> 00:13:50.537
Good evenin'. then.

133
00:13:55.084 --> 00:13:58.003
Let's not bother about the luggage.

134
00:15:21.170 --> 00:15:24.089
Hey. Morg. pretty big. isn't it?

135
00:15:27.552 --> 00:15:31.054
Oh-ho. brother. you can smell
the silver in this town.

136
00:15:33.766 --> 00:15:36.393
-Easy.
-Look at these girls over here.

137
00:15:36.477 --> 00:15:38.770
-Hi!
-Hello. girls!

138
00:15:38.855 --> 00:15:41.440
Hot damn. this burg's jumpin'!

139
00:15:41.524 --> 00:15:43.317
Here we go. ladies.

140
00:15:44.152 --> 00:15:46.695
-Isn't that sweet?
-You can say that.

141
00:15:56.706 --> 00:15:58.123
Sheriff.

142
00:16:07.216 --> 00:16:08.759
Newcomers. eh?

143
00:16:09.552 --> 00:16:12.888
The name's John Behan.
Cochise County Sheriff.

144
00:16:13.014 --> 00:16:15.057
-Just hit town. did ya?
-Just this minute.

145
00:16:15.141 --> 00:16:17.351
I'm Wyatt Earp. and these are
my brothers. Virgil and Morgan.

146
00:16:17.435 --> 00:16:19.936
Wyatt Earp. Dodge City.

147
00:16:20.063 --> 00:16:22.731
Gave all that up. Sheriff.
Goin' into business.

148
00:16:22.857 --> 00:16:26.568
-Don't even carry a gun anymore.
-Going into business. huh?

149
00:16:27.320 --> 00:16:29.905
Well. then. I'm the man to see.

150
00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:33.533
Besides sheriff. I'm also tax collector.
captain of the fire brigade

151
00:16:33.618 --> 00:16:36.328
and chairman of
the Nonpartisan Anti-Chinese League.

152
00:16:36.412 --> 00:16:38.789
-Ma'am.
-How do you do?

153
00:16:40.041 --> 00:16:42.501
Yeah. a man of many parts.

154
00:16:43.461 --> 00:16:46.004
-Say. you folks got a place to stay yet?
-No.

155
00:16:46.089 --> 00:16:49.925
-Like I said. we just got here.
-I also sit on the town lot commission.

156
00:16:51.427 --> 00:16:53.053
Really?

157
00:16:53.137 --> 00:16:57.224
As a matter of fact. we got three
lovely cottages coming up for rent.

158
00:16:57.308 --> 00:17:00.143
I'll throw in a good cleaning. no charge.

159
00:17:01.145 --> 00:17:02.479
Believe me. Mr. Earp.

160
00:17:02.563 --> 00:17:06.316
you're not gonna find a better deal
within town limits.

161
00:17:06.401 --> 00:17:08.151
I don't know. sounds pretty good.

162
00:17:08.236 --> 00:17:11.822
-I'll have my man show 'em to ya.
-Thank you.

163
00:17:18.663 --> 00:17:21.081
Hey. Wyatt. get on over here.

164
00:17:22.041 --> 00:17:24.793
I want you to meet Fred White.
He's the town marshal.

165
00:17:24.877 --> 00:17:27.045
-My pleasure.
-Lotta law around here.

166
00:17:27.130 --> 00:17:30.298
-I already met the county sheriff.
-Who. Behan?

167
00:17:30.383 --> 00:17:34.094
He ain't no law. The only real law
around here is the Cowboys.

168
00:17:34.178 --> 00:17:38.348
Cowboys? I had a run-in
with a couple of them up in Prescott.

169
00:17:38.433 --> 00:17:42.102
Nobody does nothin' without 'em.
I mean. they're it.

170
00:17:42.186 --> 00:17:44.062
There's three of 'em right over there.

171
00:17:44.147 --> 00:17:48.150
You can always spot a Cowboy.
They always wear those red sashes.

172
00:17:48.818 --> 00:17:51.027
The plain fact is the Cowboys
are good for business.

173
00:17:51.112 --> 00:17:52.904
'Bout all these saloons?

174
00:17:52.989 --> 00:17:55.615
Oh. that's the real mother lode
here in Tombstone.

175
00:17:55.700 --> 00:17:57.784
All up and down Allen Street here.

176
00:17:57.869 --> 00:18:00.996
24 hours a day.
you got liquor. hostesses. gamblin'.

177
00:18:01.080 --> 00:18:03.457
makin' money hand over fist.

178
00:18:03.541 --> 00:18:07.335
All except The Oriental.
That's a regular slaughterhouse.

179
00:18:08.254 --> 00:18:11.006
Even the high rollers won't go near it.

180
00:18:11.132 --> 00:18:13.800
That's too bad too. It's a nice place.

181
00:18:15.344 --> 00:18:17.304
Hell of a waste.

182
00:18:19.766 --> 00:18:21.224
Wyatt?

183
00:18:21.350 --> 00:18:23.518
-There he goes.
-Yeah.

184
00:18:25.271 --> 00:18:26.772
Ol' Wyatt.

185
00:18:32.862 --> 00:18:35.197
All right. fella.
I'll brace ya now for a little lesson.

186
00:18:35.323 --> 00:18:38.658
Put your money on the board.
$5 on that six of spades.

187
00:18:38.743 --> 00:18:40.994
Like that.

188
00:18:41.704 --> 00:18:45.624
I'm not gonna tell you again.
Get that cigar outta my face.

189
00:18:46.375 --> 00:18:48.293
Howdy. stranger. What can I get ya?

190
00:18:48.377 --> 00:18:50.295
I wouldn't mind one of those cigars.

191
00:18:50.379 --> 00:18:52.631
I'm about ready to go home.
I wish y'all would stop yakkin'

192
00:18:52.715 --> 00:18:55.050
-and just play cards.
-Thank you.

193
00:18:55.635 --> 00:18:58.470
Kinda nice in here. You run it?

194
00:18:58.888 --> 00:19:00.722
Milt Joyce. owner. operator.

195
00:19:00.848 --> 00:19:04.309
-Wyatt Earp.
-Yeah. sure.

196
00:19:04.393 --> 00:19:07.103
I said lay off the queen. you jackass!

197
00:19:07.188 --> 00:19:10.023
I swear I'm gonna slap somebody now.

198
00:19:10.107 --> 00:19:14.861
Excuse me for askin'. Milt.
but kinda dead in here. isn't it?

199
00:19:14.946 --> 00:19:18.782
-You don't listen too good. do ya?
-See that bird at the faro table?

200
00:19:18.908 --> 00:19:20.909
You back that queen again.
you son of a bitch.

201
00:19:20.993 --> 00:19:24.621
I'll blow you right up that wildcat's ass!
Do you hear me. huh?

202
00:19:24.747 --> 00:19:26.414
He comes bargin' in here one day.

203
00:19:26.541 --> 00:19:28.708
slappin' all the customers.
wavin' his gun around.

204
00:19:28.793 --> 00:19:31.086
He chased out all the high-class play.

205
00:19:31.170 --> 00:19:33.797
The only trade that comes in here now
is the bummers and the drovers.

206
00:19:33.881 --> 00:19:35.131
just the dregs.

207
00:19:35.258 --> 00:19:39.010
Why don't you get rid of him.
get yourself a straight dealer?

208
00:19:39.095 --> 00:19:41.179
Sure. stranger.
that's easy for you to say.

209
00:19:41.264 --> 00:19:42.722
Shit!

210
00:19:46.269 --> 00:19:48.687
Goddamn it. Junior.
how many times am I going to tell you

211
00:19:48.771 --> 00:19:52.566
to keep that damn cigar outta my face?

212
00:19:53.484 --> 00:19:55.694
Christ almighty.
it's like I'm sittin' here playing cards

213
00:19:55.778 --> 00:19:57.445
with my brother's kids or somethin'.

214
00:19:57.530 --> 00:19:59.948
you nerve-racking sons of bitches.

215
00:20:02.451 --> 00:20:04.661
Is somethin' on your mind?

216
00:20:05.454 --> 00:20:08.707
Just want to let you know
you're sittin' in my chair.

217
00:20:08.791 --> 00:20:10.792
Is that a fact?

218
00:20:10.877 --> 00:20:12.627
Yeah. it's a fact.

219
00:20:12.712 --> 00:20:16.798
For a man that don't go heeled. you run
your mouth kinda reckless. don't ya?

220
00:20:16.883 --> 00:20:20.468
No need to go heeled to get
the bulge on a dub like you.

221
00:20:21.387 --> 00:20:23.305
Is that a fact?

222
00:20:24.891 --> 00:20:26.641
That's a fact.

223
00:20:28.227 --> 00:20:31.313
Well. I'm real scared.

224
00:20:31.397 --> 00:20:35.525
Damn right. you're scared.
I can see that in your eyes.

225
00:20:35.610 --> 00:20:38.320
-All right now!
-Go ahead.

226
00:20:38.404 --> 00:20:42.490
Go ahead. skin it! Skin that
smoke wagon and see what happens.

227
00:20:45.411 --> 00:20:48.121
Listen. mister.
I'm gettin' awful tired of your...

228
00:20:48.205 --> 00:20:52.334
I'm gettin' tired of your gas.
Now jerk that pistol and go to work.

229
00:20:54.754 --> 00:20:57.005
I said throw down. boy.

230
00:21:04.680 --> 00:21:08.141
You gonna do somethin'.
or just stand there and bleed?

231
00:21:11.228 --> 00:21:12.520
No?

232
00:21:16.192 --> 00:21:17.984
I didn't think so.

233
00:21:18.694 --> 00:21:20.987
Here. Milt. a keepsake.

234
00:21:24.200 --> 00:21:28.078
Hang it over the bar.
All right. youngster. out you go.

235
00:21:30.164 --> 00:21:32.540
Don't come back!

236
00:21:32.667 --> 00:21:33.875
Ever!

237
00:21:39.173 --> 00:21:41.216
Well. what do you say. Milt?

238
00:21:41.300 --> 00:21:44.344
25% of the house take
sound about right?

239
00:21:51.352 --> 00:21:54.270
Well. we're off and runnin'.

240
00:21:54.355 --> 00:21:57.273
Just acquired us a quarter interest
in the game at the Oriental.

241
00:21:57.358 --> 00:21:59.567
-Acquired?
-So to speak.

242
00:22:03.739 --> 00:22:06.449
Now all we gotta do is keep our
eyes on that brass ring. fellas.

243
00:22:06.575 --> 00:22:08.451
You're the one. Wyatt.

244
00:22:09.161 --> 00:22:11.162
Why. Johnny Tyler!

245
00:22:12.665 --> 00:22:15.000
-You madcap!
-Doc?

246
00:22:15.543 --> 00:22:18.044
Where you goin' with that shotgun?

247
00:22:18.963 --> 00:22:21.631
I didn't know you was back in town.

248
00:22:24.176 --> 00:22:26.011
Well. well.

249
00:22:28.222 --> 00:22:29.764
How the hell are you?

250
00:22:29.849 --> 00:22:33.476
Wyatt. I am rolling. Morgan.

251
00:22:34.145 --> 00:22:36.271
-Doc.
-Virgil.

252
00:22:36.981 --> 00:22:38.773
'Lo. Doc.

253
00:22:39.191 --> 00:22:40.775
Wyatt Earp?

254
00:22:46.407 --> 00:22:48.825
Going into business for ourselves. Doc.

255
00:22:48.951 --> 00:22:52.287
Wyatt just got us a faro game.

256
00:22:52.371 --> 00:22:54.664
Since when is faro a business?

257
00:22:54.790 --> 00:22:57.208
Didn't you always say that
gambling's an honest trade?

258
00:22:57.293 --> 00:22:59.502
No. I said poker's an honest trade.

259
00:22:59.628 --> 00:23:02.505
Only suckers buck the tiger.
The odds are all on the house.

260
00:23:02.631 --> 00:23:04.007
Depends on how you look at it.

261
00:23:04.091 --> 00:23:07.218
I mean. it's not like anybody's
puttin' a gun to their head now. is it?

262
00:23:07.303 --> 00:23:11.681
That's what I love about Wyatt.
He can talk himself into anything.

263
00:23:13.476 --> 00:23:17.937
Oh. Johnny. I apologize.
I forgot you were there.

264
00:23:18.022 --> 00:23:19.814
You may go now.

265
00:23:20.566 --> 00:23:22.817
Just leave that shotgun.

266
00:23:27.323 --> 00:23:28.740
Leave it.

267
00:23:31.160 --> 00:23:32.577
Thank you.

268
00:23:36.624 --> 00:23:39.626
-Sheriff Behan!
-Gentlemen!

269
00:23:39.710 --> 00:23:42.921
Sheriff. have you met Doc Holliday?

270
00:23:43.005 --> 00:23:44.756
Piss on you. Wyatt.

271
00:23:46.008 --> 00:23:47.550
Mr. Holliday.

272
00:23:50.179 --> 00:23:52.931
Forgive me if I don't shake hands.

273
00:23:55.184 --> 00:23:57.936
-So. how's our little town suit you?
-Fine. Fine.

274
00:23:58.020 --> 00:24:01.689
You know. I was thinking. what this
town could really use is a racetrack.

275
00:24:01.774 --> 00:24:06.444
Really? That's not a bad idea.
Send a signal we're growin' up.

276
00:24:06.529 --> 00:24:07.946
Way ahead of yourselves.
aren't you. boys?

277
00:24:08.030 --> 00:24:10.156
This is just another mining camp.

278
00:24:10.241 --> 00:24:13.868
Have you seen how everyone dresses?
Awful tony for a mining camp.

279
00:24:13.953 --> 00:24:15.995
No sir. the die is cast. We are growin'.

280
00:24:16.080 --> 00:24:19.874
Be as big as San Francisco in
a few years. and just as sophisticated.

281
00:24:22.211 --> 00:24:23.920
You son of a bitch!

282
00:24:24.004 --> 00:24:26.965
Easy. gents! It's a private affair!

283
00:24:27.049 --> 00:24:28.633
Don't raise that iron.
I don't wanna have to...

284
00:24:28.717 --> 00:24:31.553
I'll kill you. you cheatin' son of a...

285
00:24:33.889 --> 00:24:35.932
Very cosmopolitan.

286
00:24:37.560 --> 00:24:40.228
I know him. That's Creek Johnson.

287
00:24:43.524 --> 00:24:45.900
Wyatt? Doc?

288
00:24:47.653 --> 00:24:50.238
-Jack.
-What do you say. old friend?

289
00:24:52.741 --> 00:24:55.243
What the hell's that all about. Creek?

290
00:24:55.327 --> 00:24:58.204
He crawfished a bet
and called me a liar.

291
00:24:58.289 --> 00:25:01.499
Sheriff. may I present
a pair of fellow sophisticates.

292
00:25:01.584 --> 00:25:03.126
Turkey Creek Jack Johnson.

293
00:25:03.210 --> 00:25:05.420
Texas Jack Vermillion.

294
00:25:05.546 --> 00:25:07.547
Watch your ear. Creek.

295
00:25:09.175 --> 00:25:13.052
-Afraid I'll have to have those guns.
-It was a fair fight. We was legal.

296
00:25:13.137 --> 00:25:16.055
I'm sorry. boys.
I gotta take you before Judge Spicer.

297
00:25:16.140 --> 00:25:17.807
Hand 'em over.

298
00:25:18.642 --> 00:25:20.643
Law and order every time. that's us.

299
00:25:36.535 --> 00:25:38.161
I'm frightfully thirsty.

300
00:25:38.287 --> 00:25:41.164
Well. we made it safe and sound.

301
00:25:46.295 --> 00:25:48.796
Sheriff. what kinda town is this?

302
00:25:52.968 --> 00:25:54.677
Nice scenery.

303
00:26:00.517 --> 00:26:04.437
Well. an enchanted moment.

304
00:26:10.486 --> 00:26:14.822
Interesting little scene.
I wonder who that tall drink of water is.

305
00:26:15.407 --> 00:26:18.826
My dear. you have set your gaze
upon the quintessential frontier type.

306
00:26:18.953 --> 00:26:23.748
Note the lean silhouette. eyes closed
by the sun. though sharp as a hawk.

307
00:26:23.832 --> 00:26:27.210
He's got the look of
both predator and prey.

308
00:26:27.795 --> 00:26:29.796
I want one.

309
00:26:29.880 --> 00:26:31.673
Happy hunting.

310
00:26:58.158 --> 00:27:00.410
Hey there. sister boy!

311
00:27:00.995 --> 00:27:02.495
Please. sister boy. gimme some!

312
00:27:02.579 --> 00:27:05.790
-Gimme. gimme. gimme!
-Leave him alone. Barnes!

313
00:27:05.874 --> 00:27:08.793
Billy. sit with me.

314
00:27:15.676 --> 00:27:19.595
This is so much fun. We haven't
been to a show since years.

315
00:27:19.722 --> 00:27:22.307
I hope they're good.

316
00:27:24.518 --> 00:27:27.145
-Wyatt?
-Oh. sorry.

317
00:27:30.816 --> 00:27:33.067
Darlin'. you know the Earps.

318
00:27:33.986 --> 00:27:36.195
Kate. how you been?

319
00:27:37.698 --> 00:27:40.575
Mattie. ravishin'.

320
00:27:40.659 --> 00:27:42.118
Doc.

321
00:27:44.913 --> 00:27:48.499
Wyatt. I'd like ya
to meet Mayor Clum and his wife.

322
00:27:48.584 --> 00:27:49.834
-Mr. Earp.
-Mayor.

323
00:27:49.918 --> 00:27:51.836
Your reputation precedes you.

324
00:27:51.920 --> 00:27:56.132
-I was wondering if you might be...
-Not a prayer. Nice meetin' you.

325
00:28:09.063 --> 00:28:12.690
Professor Gillman? Oh. I seen him
in Bisbee. He catches stuff.

326
00:28:12.775 --> 00:28:15.276
Hey. Professor. catch this.

327
00:28:17.988 --> 00:28:21.491
They're shooting at us!
They're actually shooting at us.

328
00:28:22.409 --> 00:28:25.453
At least we won't have to wait
for our notices.

329
00:28:26.455 --> 00:28:28.915
Prettiest man I ever saw.

330
00:28:33.003 --> 00:28:34.295
Ladies and gentlemen.

331
00:28:34.380 --> 00:28:36.923
the St. Crispin's Day
speech from Henry V.

332
00:28:37.007 --> 00:28:38.758
To set the scene...

333
00:28:39.343 --> 00:28:42.553
-Goddamn. Barnes!
-Almost shot my damn ear off.

334
00:28:42.638 --> 00:28:45.098
"If we are marked to die.

335
00:28:45.182 --> 00:28:47.975
"we are now to do our country loss.

336
00:28:48.060 --> 00:28:52.772
"But if to live. the fewer men.
the greater share of honor."

337
00:28:52.856 --> 00:28:56.526
He's got some nerve. I'll say that.
What d'ya think there. Billy Nilly?

338
00:28:56.652 --> 00:28:58.569
I think he's wonderful.

339
00:28:59.363 --> 00:29:01.572
"...gentle his condition.

340
00:29:01.657 --> 00:29:04.033
"Gentlemen in England now abed shall
think themselves accurs'd

341
00:29:04.118 --> 00:29:06.202
"they were not here.

342
00:29:06.328 --> 00:29:08.830
"and hold their manhoods cheap

343
00:29:08.914 --> 00:29:13.418
"whilst any speaks who fought with us
upon Saint Crispin's day."

344
00:29:13.961 --> 00:29:16.754
That's great! That's our kinda stuff!

345
00:29:25.681 --> 00:29:26.722
Play it again!

346
00:29:36.692 --> 00:29:39.527
Now what in the hell is this?

347
00:29:39.611 --> 00:29:43.030
That's Faust.
He's gonna make a deal with the devil.

348
00:29:45.617 --> 00:29:47.869
Is your soul for sale. dear?

349
00:30:02.551 --> 00:30:04.510
Know what I'd do?

350
00:30:04.595 --> 00:30:08.973
I'd take a deal and then crawfish
and drill that old devil in the ass.

351
00:30:11.310 --> 00:30:14.228
How 'bout you. Juanito?
What would you do?

352
00:30:15.564 --> 00:30:17.231
I already did it.

353
00:30:37.377 --> 00:30:39.086
Very instructive.

354
00:30:46.929 --> 00:30:48.888
But who was the devil?

355
00:31:02.152 --> 00:31:03.945
I'll be damned.

356
00:31:05.364 --> 00:31:07.907
You may indeed. if you get lucky.

357
00:31:13.622 --> 00:31:15.498
Would you look at all those stars?

358
00:31:15.624 --> 00:31:19.961
I mean. you look up and you think.
"God made all of that?

359
00:31:20.045 --> 00:31:23.214
"He still remembered to make
a little speck like me."

360
00:31:23.298 --> 00:31:26.217
Kinda flattering. really.

361
00:31:26.301 --> 00:31:28.970
Wyatt. do you believe in God?

362
00:31:29.096 --> 00:31:33.683
-No. come on. really. Do ya?
-Yeah. Maybe. Hell. I don't know.

363
00:31:33.767 --> 00:31:35.977
Well. what d'you think
happens when you die?

364
00:31:36.103 --> 00:31:38.437
Somethin'. Nothin'. Hell. I don't know.

365
00:31:38.522 --> 00:31:41.232
Well. I read this book.
a book on spiritualism.

366
00:31:41.316 --> 00:31:43.776
Oh. God. here he goes again.

367
00:31:43.860 --> 00:31:47.029
Said that a lot of people
when they die. they see this light.

368
00:31:47.114 --> 00:31:49.490
-Like in a tunnel.
-Yeah?

369
00:31:49.616 --> 00:31:51.158
They say it's the light
leadin' you to heaven.

370
00:31:51.243 --> 00:31:52.285
Really?

371
00:31:52.369 --> 00:31:54.537
Well. what about hell?
They got a sign there. or what?

372
00:31:54.663 --> 00:31:55.871
Hey. Wyatt. goddamn it.

373
00:31:55.956 --> 00:31:58.249
-I'm serious.
-Hey. Morg.

374
00:31:58.333 --> 00:31:59.792
Comin' to the Oriental. Virg?

375
00:31:59.876 --> 00:32:02.086
-Well.
-Not tonight.

376
00:32:02.170 --> 00:32:04.964
Tonight. me and my old man
are gonna have some fun.

377
00:32:05.048 --> 00:32:07.091
Come on. get movin'. old man.

378
00:32:07.175 --> 00:32:10.094
Maiden name was Sullivan.

379
00:32:12.681 --> 00:32:15.933
Well. you better go with them. honey.
I gotta go to work.

380
00:32:16.018 --> 00:32:17.852
Please stay with me.

381
00:32:17.936 --> 00:32:20.438
Well. honey. I gotta get to work.

382
00:32:21.440 --> 00:32:24.650
All right. All right.

383
00:32:25.027 --> 00:32:28.279
Well. wait a minute.
I guess I don't have to go right now. I...

384
00:32:28.363 --> 00:32:30.906
-I could stay awhile.
-No. no. I don't wanna keep you.

385
00:32:31.033 --> 00:32:33.534
No. really. I can stay awhile.

386
00:32:35.537 --> 00:32:37.872
That the bottle Lou gave you?

387
00:32:38.707 --> 00:32:40.333
Yes. it is.

388
00:32:41.918 --> 00:32:44.211
Maybe you should see a doctor.

389
00:32:45.464 --> 00:32:47.923
Wyatt. it's just headaches.

390
00:32:48.717 --> 00:32:51.135
I know what I'm doing.
No. I don't need to see a doctor!

391
00:32:51.219 --> 00:32:53.804
-All right. honey. Okay.
-Just go.

392
00:32:54.890 --> 00:32:57.016
Everything's fine. Wyatt.

393
00:32:57.100 --> 00:33:00.227
-Work well.
-All right. good night.

394
00:33:02.731 --> 00:33:05.191
You look beautiful tonight.

395
00:33:06.777 --> 00:33:08.361
Thank you.

396
00:33:10.781 --> 00:33:13.741
-Night. Mattie.
-Good night. Morgan.

397
00:33:17.079 --> 00:33:18.412
Come on.

398
00:33:22.918 --> 00:33:25.920
I want to match seven.
seven stinkin' spades.

399
00:33:26.004 --> 00:33:27.838
-Let's go.
-I'm your man.

400
00:33:27.923 --> 00:33:31.008
You win again. Well played. sir.
You are on fire.

401
00:33:31.093 --> 00:33:33.260
-I told you. I'm burnin' up tonight.
-Loser on the ace.

402
00:33:33.345 --> 00:33:36.931
I'll take the red seven.
and I got some deeds here.

403
00:33:37.057 --> 00:33:40.685
-I'll take seven stinkin' diamonds.
-Awful lot of money.

404
00:33:40.769 --> 00:33:42.728
You can't stand the heat. pal.
get out of the kitchen.

405
00:33:42.813 --> 00:33:43.896
You're the doctor.

406
00:33:43.980 --> 00:33:46.107
Sad news. friend. you lose.

407
00:33:47.234 --> 00:33:50.069
-So. now we're in the mining business.
-You're the one. Wyatt.

408
00:33:50.153 --> 00:33:52.655
We're turnin' into regular tycoons.

409
00:33:52.739 --> 00:33:54.532
Think I'll call this one
the Mattie Blaylock.

410
00:33:54.616 --> 00:33:55.825
Mattie'd get a kick outta that one.

411
00:33:55.909 --> 00:33:58.494
-That's her maiden name.
-And what a maiden.

412
00:33:58.620 --> 00:34:01.497
-Pure as the driven snow. I'm sure.
-Hey. Doc. come on now.

413
00:34:01.623 --> 00:34:05.126
It's just his style. Morg.
He doesn't mean anything.

414
00:34:05.252 --> 00:34:07.837
Tell me something. my friend.
I'm curious.

415
00:34:07.921 --> 00:34:12.800
Do you actually consider yourself
a married man. forsaking all others?

416
00:34:12.884 --> 00:34:14.552
Yeah. pretty much.

417
00:34:14.636 --> 00:34:18.472
I mean. I was no angel
when we met. but neither was she.

418
00:34:18.557 --> 00:34:22.727
People can change. Doc.
Sooner or later. you gotta grow up.

419
00:34:23.228 --> 00:34:24.478
I see.

420
00:34:25.814 --> 00:34:28.899
And what would you do.
if she walked in here?

421
00:34:29.484 --> 00:34:33.654
-"She"?
-You know damn well who I mean.

422
00:34:34.239 --> 00:34:36.615
That dusky-hued
lady satan. that's who.

423
00:34:36.700 --> 00:34:38.951
-Oh. I'd probably ignore her.
-Ignore her?

424
00:34:39.035 --> 00:34:41.954
I'd ignore her. People can change. Doc.

425
00:34:42.038 --> 00:34:44.373
I'll remember you said that.

426
00:34:45.167 --> 00:34:46.375
What?

427
00:34:49.755 --> 00:34:53.758
-Bravo! Bravo!
-Ma'am? Miss Marcus?

428
00:34:53.842 --> 00:34:55.259
Aw. hell.

429
00:34:59.347 --> 00:35:01.348
Bravo!

430
00:35:20.952 --> 00:35:23.579
Miss Marcus. allow me
the pleasure of a drink.

431
00:35:23.663 --> 00:35:26.582
-Thank you. sir.
-Milt. champagne!

432
00:35:27.375 --> 00:35:28.542
Satisfied?

433
00:35:28.627 --> 00:35:31.837
I stand corrected. Wyatt. You're an oak.

434
00:35:44.059 --> 00:35:45.559
Thanks. Kate.

435
00:35:56.029 --> 00:35:57.613
Mr. Fabian.

436
00:35:58.114 --> 00:35:59.532
-Well done.
-Well done.

437
00:35:59.616 --> 00:36:01.450
Good show. partner. good show.

438
00:36:01.576 --> 00:36:04.411
Mr. Fabian. would you
come sit at my table?

439
00:36:05.872 --> 00:36:08.374
Mr. Earp. would you mind signing
an autograph for me. sir?

440
00:36:10.460 --> 00:36:12.920
My wife's not gonna believe this.

441
00:36:18.510 --> 00:36:22.096
Wyatt Earp. huh? Heard of you.

442
00:36:24.266 --> 00:36:27.268
Listen now. Mr. Kansas Law Dog.

443
00:36:27.352 --> 00:36:29.979
Law don't go around here. Savvy?

444
00:36:30.647 --> 00:36:33.774
-I'm retired.
-Good.

445
00:36:33.859 --> 00:36:35.818
That's real good.

446
00:36:35.902 --> 00:36:40.322
Yeah. Yeah. that's real good. law dog.
'cause law just don't go around here.

447
00:36:40.448 --> 00:36:41.866
Yeah. I heard you the first time.

448
00:36:41.950 --> 00:36:44.201
Winner to the king. $500.

449
00:36:48.456 --> 00:36:52.710
-Shut up. Ike.
-You must be Doc Holliday.

450
00:36:54.754 --> 00:36:56.630
That's the rumor.

451
00:36:56.715 --> 00:36:58.465
You retired too?

452
00:37:00.135 --> 00:37:02.761
Not me. I'm in my prime.

453
00:37:03.763 --> 00:37:05.472
Yeah. you look it.

454
00:37:08.476 --> 00:37:11.103
You must be Ringo.

455
00:37:11.187 --> 00:37:14.398
Look. darlin'. Johnny Ringo.

456
00:37:14.482 --> 00:37:17.985
the deadliest pistoleer
since Wild Bill. they say.

457
00:37:20.322 --> 00:37:23.115
What do you think. darlin'.
should I hate him?

458
00:37:23.199 --> 00:37:27.453
-You don't even know him.
-No. That's true. but...

459
00:37:27.537 --> 00:37:31.248
I don't know.
there's just somethin' about him.

460
00:37:31.333 --> 00:37:33.542
Somethin' 'round the eyes.

461
00:37:35.420 --> 00:37:37.046
I don't know.

462
00:37:37.172 --> 00:37:38.839
Reminds me of...

463
00:37:39.841 --> 00:37:41.008
Me.

464
00:37:42.594 --> 00:37:45.679
No. I'm sure of it. I hate him.

465
00:37:46.681 --> 00:37:48.349
He's drunk.

466
00:38:11.539 --> 00:38:16.043
Come on. boys. we don't want any
trouble in here. not in any language.

467
00:38:16.628 --> 00:38:18.295
That's Latin. darlin'.

468
00:38:18.380 --> 00:38:21.131
Evidently. Mr. Ringo's
an educated man.

469
00:38:22.634 --> 00:38:24.760
Now I really hate him.

470
00:38:25.887 --> 00:38:27.554
Watch it. Johnny.

471
00:38:28.556 --> 00:38:30.766
I hear he's real fast.

472
00:38:40.443 --> 00:38:42.569
Come on. Go. Johnny.

473
00:39:44.466 --> 00:39:45.924
Bravo!

474
00:39:55.560 --> 00:39:57.227
Drinks are on me!

475
00:40:04.861 --> 00:40:07.696
Gettin' kinda spooky around here.

476
00:40:07.781 --> 00:40:09.740
Curly Bill. huh?

477
00:40:10.158 --> 00:40:13.619
-Who was that other idiot?
-Ike Clanton.

478
00:40:13.703 --> 00:40:17.331
-Table's open!
-The man dealing faro. who is he?

479
00:40:17.832 --> 00:40:22.836
That's Wyatt Earp. Made a name for
himself as a peace officer in Kansas.

480
00:40:24.506 --> 00:40:26.465
Peace officer.

481
00:40:26.549 --> 00:40:28.258
Very impressive.

482
00:40:31.429 --> 00:40:33.722
I believe he's married.

483
00:40:37.018 --> 00:40:38.852
More champagne?

484
00:40:55.036 --> 00:40:56.829
Oh. hell.

485
00:41:05.713 --> 00:41:07.548
-Hello.
-Hello.

486
00:41:08.967 --> 00:41:11.635
We've never actually met.
My name is...

487
00:41:11.719 --> 00:41:13.887
Wyatt Earp. Yes. I know.

488
00:41:13.972 --> 00:41:16.265
-I'm...
-Josephine Marcus.

489
00:41:17.308 --> 00:41:19.059
Everybody knows.

490
00:41:20.061 --> 00:41:22.312
I was beginning to think
we'd never meet.

491
00:41:22.397 --> 00:41:25.566
This is fortuitous. That means "lucky."

492
00:41:26.442 --> 00:41:28.652
Yeah. I know what it means.

493
00:41:30.363 --> 00:41:32.447
-Easy now.
-What is it?

494
00:41:32.532 --> 00:41:34.491
That mare is in season.

495
00:41:35.451 --> 00:41:37.369
Bet she's starting.

496
00:41:37.620 --> 00:41:41.874
-How do they know?
-They know. It's the scent.

497
00:41:46.129 --> 00:41:47.963
Well. I guess we'd better split 'em up.
It's been real...

498
00:41:48.089 --> 00:41:49.590
I have a better idea.

499
00:41:49.716 --> 00:41:51.925
Let's run it out of them.

500
00:41:54.137 --> 00:41:56.096
Yeah. I'm an oak. all right.

501
00:42:40.016 --> 00:42:42.601
Well. end of the road.

502
00:42:42.685 --> 00:42:44.186
Maybe for you.

503
00:43:06.542 --> 00:43:07.918
That was lovely.

504
00:43:08.002 --> 00:43:11.046
Lovely? You could've been
killed back there. or busted up.

505
00:43:11.172 --> 00:43:13.257
Fun. though. wasn't it?

506
00:43:13.341 --> 00:43:16.260
-You'd die for fun?
-Wouldn't you?

507
00:43:18.137 --> 00:43:21.348
Oh. he's laughing.
I didn't think you ever laughed.

508
00:43:21.432 --> 00:43:23.600
Yeah. I laugh sometimes.

509
00:43:23.685 --> 00:43:26.270
Yes. but how often? Are you happy?

510
00:43:26.854 --> 00:43:31.024
Am I happy? Well. I don't know.
I'm happy as the next man. I guess.

511
00:43:31.859 --> 00:43:35.487
I don't laugh all day long like an idiot.
if that's what you mean.

512
00:43:35.571 --> 00:43:38.282
-Touchy about it. aren't you?
-No. I'm not touchy. I'm just...

513
00:43:38.366 --> 00:43:39.866
It's a silly question. is all.

514
00:43:39.951 --> 00:43:42.369
"Am I happy? Are you happy?"
Are you happy?

515
00:43:42.453 --> 00:43:45.497
Oh. I'm always happy.
unless I'm bored.

516
00:43:46.291 --> 00:43:49.209
That blonde woman. is that your wife?

517
00:43:51.546 --> 00:43:53.714
-What about her?
-Nothing.

518
00:43:55.091 --> 00:43:57.342
What do you want out of life?

519
00:44:01.055 --> 00:44:03.223
-How do you get these questions?
-Just answer.

520
00:44:03.308 --> 00:44:05.309
I don't know!
Make some money. I guess.

521
00:44:05.393 --> 00:44:08.895
-Maybe have some children.
-Doesn't suit you.

522
00:44:09.981 --> 00:44:12.983
-Well. how would you know?
-It just doesn't. that's all.

523
00:44:13.067 --> 00:44:14.609
I oughta know my own mind.

524
00:44:14.694 --> 00:44:17.070
and I'm telling you what suits me
is a family and kids.

525
00:44:17.196 --> 00:44:20.324
Suits me right down to the ground.
In fact. that's my idea of heaven.

526
00:44:20.408 --> 00:44:22.743
All right. what's your idea of heaven?

527
00:44:22.827 --> 00:44:24.286
Room service.

528
00:44:26.414 --> 00:44:29.666
Oh. he's laughing again.
Well. that's what I want.

529
00:44:30.710 --> 00:44:34.254
I wanna move and go places
and never look back.

530
00:44:34.339 --> 00:44:36.590
Just have fun. forever.

531
00:44:36.716 --> 00:44:40.802
That's my idea of heaven.
Need someone to share it with. though.

532
00:44:42.638 --> 00:44:44.473
You mean Behan.

533
00:44:47.268 --> 00:44:49.019
Well. then...

534
00:44:51.230 --> 00:44:52.731
Why are you with him?

535
00:44:52.815 --> 00:44:57.110
Because he's handsome
and he's charming and...

536
00:44:57.236 --> 00:44:59.196
He's all right. For now.

537
00:45:00.573 --> 00:45:03.116
Oh. I know. don't say it. I'm rotten.

538
00:45:03.201 --> 00:45:07.079
I've tried to be good. It's just so boring.

539
00:45:07.163 --> 00:45:09.414
The way you talk.

540
00:45:09.499 --> 00:45:12.793
Never heard a woman talk like that?

541
00:45:14.337 --> 00:45:15.754
Never.

542
00:45:16.631 --> 00:45:20.217
I don't have time to be proper.
I wanna live.

543
00:45:21.636 --> 00:45:23.845
I'm a woman. I like men.

544
00:45:23.930 --> 00:45:28.266
If that means I'm not ladylike.
then I guess I'm just not a lady.

545
00:45:28.351 --> 00:45:31.103
-At least I'm honest.
-You're different.

546
00:45:32.814 --> 00:45:35.524
There's no arguin' that.

547
00:45:35.608 --> 00:45:37.943
But you're a lady. all right.

548
00:45:39.821 --> 00:45:41.822
I'll take my oath on it.

549
00:45:46.369 --> 00:45:48.787
Come on! Giddap!

550
00:46:05.680 --> 00:46:08.014
Is that the opium Lou gave you?

551
00:46:11.144 --> 00:46:13.353
It's a new bottle. isn't it?

552
00:46:15.022 --> 00:46:17.482
You better go easy on that stuff.

553
00:46:17.567 --> 00:46:19.526
Wyatt. leave me alone.

554
00:46:21.446 --> 00:46:25.824
-And where've you been?
-Just out. Ridin'.

555
00:46:31.831 --> 00:46:33.999
How're you feelin'. Mattie?

556
00:46:39.046 --> 00:46:41.089
I don't know.

557
00:46:41.382 --> 00:46:42.924
I'm all right.

558
00:46:44.594 --> 00:46:46.386
I'm fine.

559
00:46:47.555 --> 00:46:50.223
-You sure?
-I'm sure.

560
00:46:51.934 --> 00:46:55.395
Well. I was thinkin' today.

561
00:46:56.772 --> 00:46:59.774
we've already made
a pile of money in this place.

562
00:46:59.859 --> 00:47:02.194
If we pulled up stakes
and just moved on. you know.

563
00:47:02.278 --> 00:47:05.030
then we could stay on the move.
keep goin'. see the world.

564
00:47:05.114 --> 00:47:08.992
Just live on room service
for the rest of our lives.

565
00:47:09.076 --> 00:47:10.911
How'd that be?

566
00:47:11.496 --> 00:47:13.538
Room service?

567
00:47:16.167 --> 00:47:18.585
Wyatt. what're you talkin' about?

568
00:47:23.257 --> 00:47:25.008
Nothin'. I just...

569
00:47:25.092 --> 00:47:28.011
Just thinkin' out loud. and you know I...

570
00:47:29.847 --> 00:47:31.473
Nothin'.

571
00:47:34.310 --> 00:47:36.102
Forget about it.

572
00:47:56.374 --> 00:47:58.875
What's she doin' with that lunger?

573
00:48:10.263 --> 00:48:15.433
Hey.

574
00:48:16.686 --> 00:48:20.772
Is that Old Dog Tray?
That sounds like Old Dog Tray to me.

575
00:48:22.316 --> 00:48:23.567
Pardon?

576
00:48:24.986 --> 00:48:27.320
You know. Stephen Foster.

577
00:48:28.155 --> 00:48:30.282
Oh! Susanna.

578
00:48:30.366 --> 00:48:32.409
Camptown Races.

579
00:48:35.079 --> 00:48:37.372
Stephen stinkin' Foster!

580
00:48:38.165 --> 00:48:42.127
Yes. well.
this happens to be a nocturne.

581
00:48:43.087 --> 00:48:45.922
-A which?
-You know.

582
00:48:46.007 --> 00:48:48.258
Frederic fucking Chopin.

583
00:48:59.437 --> 00:49:01.021
Oh. yeah.

584
00:49:15.870 --> 00:49:18.371
Boy. I feel great.

585
00:49:20.666 --> 00:49:24.544
I feel just capital.

586
00:49:55.868 --> 00:49:58.411
Do you see what's going on
in the street?

587
00:49:58.496 --> 00:50:01.331
-Somebody's gotta do something.
-I believe you're the sheriff.

588
00:50:01.415 --> 00:50:05.585
No. no. This is not county business.
This is a town matter. Marshal?

589
00:50:09.632 --> 00:50:11.633
Why don't you just leave it alone?

590
00:50:11.717 --> 00:50:15.428
No. I gotta do somethin'.

591
00:50:20.434 --> 00:50:22.435
Here's your down card.

592
00:50:41.872 --> 00:50:43.289
Curly Bill!

593
00:50:47.294 --> 00:50:48.795
Come on now.

594
00:50:50.464 --> 00:50:52.340
Well. howdy. Fred.

595
00:50:53.259 --> 00:50:55.969
Hand those over. Curly. Hand 'em over.

596
00:51:00.057 --> 00:51:02.183
Why. sure. dad.

597
00:51:04.437 --> 00:51:06.563
I'm only funnin'.

598
00:51:07.857 --> 00:51:09.441
Here you go.

599
00:51:21.829 --> 00:51:23.288
Fred?

600
00:51:24.290 --> 00:51:26.124
Come on now. Fred?

601
00:51:30.588 --> 00:51:33.965
-Got ol' Fred White!
-Hey. he shot the marshal! Everybody!

602
00:51:34.049 --> 00:51:36.342
Better get him off the street.

603
00:51:38.012 --> 00:51:40.930
Fred White's dead! They killed him.
They killed Fred White!

604
00:51:41.015 --> 00:51:45.351
-All right. back off.
-Get a rope! String him up!

605
00:51:45.436 --> 00:51:48.104
-Nobody's hangin' anybody.
-He just killed a man!

606
00:51:48.189 --> 00:51:51.399
Then he'll stand trial for it.
Now get back! Move!

607
00:51:55.696 --> 00:51:57.238
Turn him loose!

608
00:52:05.831 --> 00:52:08.666
He said to turn loose of him.

609
00:52:08.751 --> 00:52:11.961
Well. I'm not. So go home.

610
00:52:12.755 --> 00:52:17.967
I swear to God. law dog. you don't
step aside. we'll tear you apart.

611
00:52:18.052 --> 00:52:21.304
All right. you die first. Get it?

612
00:52:21.972 --> 00:52:23.389
Your friends might get me in a rush.

613
00:52:23.474 --> 00:52:27.143
but not before I make your head
into a canoe. You understand me?

614
00:52:27.228 --> 00:52:30.897
-He's bluffin'. Let's rush him.
-No. he ain't bluffin'.

615
00:52:32.191 --> 00:52:34.859
You're not as stupid as you look. Ike.

616
00:52:35.444 --> 00:52:38.738
-Now tell them to get back.
-Go on now. get back.

617
00:52:38.823 --> 00:52:41.407
Go on! Billy!

618
00:52:42.743 --> 00:52:44.536
He'll kill me.

619
00:52:48.582 --> 00:52:51.292
And you. music lover.

620
00:52:52.294 --> 00:52:53.753
you're next.

621
00:52:55.172 --> 00:52:58.174
It's the drunk piano player.

622
00:52:58.259 --> 00:53:00.969
You're so drunk. you can't hit nothin'.

623
00:53:01.053 --> 00:53:04.472
In fact. you're probably seein' double.

624
00:53:04.598 --> 00:53:08.434
I have two guns. one for each of ya.

625
00:53:11.063 --> 00:53:13.147
All right. break it up now!

626
00:53:17.945 --> 00:53:19.487
Go home now!

627
00:53:31.166 --> 00:53:32.876
I'll see you soon.

628
00:53:34.628 --> 00:53:37.422
-I'll see you soon.
-We'll meet again.

629
00:53:42.678 --> 00:53:44.804
Well. as you can see.

630
00:53:45.806 --> 00:53:47.640
never a dull moment.

631
00:54:13.667 --> 00:54:16.085
So it takes Judge Spicer
three weeks to get back to town.

632
00:54:16.170 --> 00:54:18.838
and he says.
"Well. did you actually see it?"

633
00:54:18.923 --> 00:54:22.884
I said. "No. By the time I got there.
Marshal White had already been shot."

634
00:54:22.968 --> 00:54:24.886
Then Spicer leans forward
and he says.

635
00:54:24.970 --> 00:54:28.264
"Well. can't have a murder
without a witness."

636
00:54:28.349 --> 00:54:31.142
-What?
-Case dismissed. Can you beat it?

637
00:54:31.352 --> 00:54:35.021
After all that? Aw. hell. who cares?

638
00:54:35.105 --> 00:54:37.565
None of my business anyway.

639
00:54:37.858 --> 00:54:40.234
There you go. Milt.

640
00:54:40.319 --> 00:54:44.238
God. I love this game!
You know. boys. when we're finally set.

641
00:54:44.990 --> 00:54:48.159
we gotta each have
a billiard room in our houses.

642
00:54:48.243 --> 00:54:49.619
I been thinkin'.

643
00:54:49.703 --> 00:54:52.997
maybe we oughta open up
a place of our own. You know?

644
00:54:53.082 --> 00:54:56.209
There's the real money. Build it up.

645
00:54:56.293 --> 00:54:58.836
milk it for all it's worth.
then sell it off for a bundle.

646
00:54:58.921 --> 00:55:01.130
and breeze outta this burg
with more money than Croesus

647
00:55:01.215 --> 00:55:02.715
and ready to live like kings.

648
00:55:02.800 --> 00:55:04.968
What d'ya think. Virg?

649
00:55:08.722 --> 00:55:10.932
Virg? Why don't you and me
take a walk around town

650
00:55:11.058 --> 00:55:14.477
and see if we can't spot us out
a couple of nice lots?

651
00:55:16.855 --> 00:55:19.899
It's workin' out just like you said. Wyatt.

652
00:55:19.984 --> 00:55:22.944
Goddamn. boys. we're lootin'
this burg six ways from Sunday.

653
00:55:23.028 --> 00:55:24.320
Pretty fun too. isn't it?

654
00:55:24.405 --> 00:55:26.781
Financially. yeah. I gotta admit.

655
00:55:26.907 --> 00:55:29.075
Excuse me.
Wyatt. do you have a moment?

656
00:55:29.159 --> 00:55:31.452
-Please. will you just hear me out?
-Now hold on. Mayor.

657
00:55:31.578 --> 00:55:32.578
He already told you no.

658
00:55:32.663 --> 00:55:35.373
You tell him. Morg.

659
00:55:35.457 --> 00:55:37.959
What about you? You were a lawman.

660
00:55:40.921 --> 00:55:42.714
I'm busy.

661
00:55:43.090 --> 00:55:44.924
We're all busy.

662
00:55:46.051 --> 00:55:49.303
Sorry. Mayor.
but you're barkin' up the wrong tree.

663
00:55:49.388 --> 00:55:52.056
You know. you men are makin'
a lot of money in this town.

664
00:55:52.141 --> 00:55:54.851
That's good. That's good.
Good for you.

665
00:55:54.935 --> 00:55:58.187
In the meantime. a lot of
decent people are suffering.

666
00:55:58.272 --> 00:56:02.942
But. please. don't let me take up
any more of your precious time.

667
00:56:07.031 --> 00:56:09.198
Rack 'em.

668
00:56:09.283 --> 00:56:12.744
I tell ya. I'm suffering.
From a hangover.

669
00:56:21.336 --> 00:56:22.462
Stop that!

670
00:56:22.546 --> 00:56:25.548
-Stop.
-No.

671
00:57:20.604 --> 00:57:24.023
Hold on a minute! Wait a minute!

672
00:57:24.149 --> 00:57:27.360
-Calm down and listen to me!
-Yeah. let him speak!

673
00:57:27.444 --> 00:57:30.238
Nobody's sayin' you can't own a gun.

674
00:57:30.364 --> 00:57:33.407
Nobody's even sayin'
you can't carry a gun.

675
00:57:33.492 --> 00:57:36.869
All we're sayin' is you
can't carry a gun in town.

676
00:57:41.083 --> 00:57:43.334
That's not so bad. is it?

677
00:57:49.550 --> 00:57:52.051
Listen. Mayor. I have
to talk to you about this.

678
00:57:52.136 --> 00:57:55.221
No. we don't have to talk.
You can read. can't you?

679
00:57:55.305 --> 00:57:56.347
It's a town matter. not county.

680
00:57:56.431 --> 00:58:00.560
What in the hell are you doin'?
I told you we weren't gettin' involved.

681
00:58:00.644 --> 00:58:03.688
You got us involved
when you brought us here.

682
00:58:04.439 --> 00:58:06.816
Now you hold on a minute. Virg.

683
00:58:06.900 --> 00:58:10.444
Hold on nothin'! I walk around this
town and look these people in the eye.

684
00:58:10.529 --> 00:58:13.072
It's just like someone's
slappin' me in the face.

685
00:58:13.157 --> 00:58:15.032
These people are afraid
to walk down the street.

686
00:58:15.117 --> 00:58:18.661
and I'm tryin' to make money off that
like some goddamn vulture!

687
00:58:18.745 --> 00:58:20.163
If we're gonna have
a future in this town.

688
00:58:20.247 --> 00:58:21.706
it's gotta have some law and order.

689
00:58:21.790 --> 00:58:24.167
Please. Virg. don't do this to me!

690
00:58:24.251 --> 00:58:26.210
It's got nothin' to do with you!
It's got to do with...

691
00:58:26.295 --> 00:58:27.503
Nothin' to do with me?

692
00:58:27.588 --> 00:58:30.756
I'm your brother. for Christ's sake!
God. I don't believe this!

693
00:58:30.841 --> 00:58:33.384
Talk to him. will you? Or hit him!

694
00:58:37.222 --> 00:58:39.682
Ah. God. don't tell me!

695
00:58:39.766 --> 00:58:42.059
Like you said. Wyatt. we're brothers.

696
00:58:42.144 --> 00:58:46.314
Gotta back your brother's play.
Just did like I figured you would.

697
00:58:46.899 --> 00:58:49.901
All right now.
you listen to me. both of ya!

698
00:58:52.112 --> 00:58:53.196
For the first time in our lives.

699
00:58:53.280 --> 00:58:55.865
we got a chance to stop wandering
and finally be a family.

700
00:58:55.949 --> 00:58:59.660
This is trouble we don't need.
You saw what happened to Fred White.

701
00:58:59.745 --> 00:59:02.121
We know what we're doin'. Wyatt.

702
00:59:02.247 --> 00:59:05.875
Okay. fine. Say you're right.
say you don't get yourself killed.

703
00:59:05.959 --> 00:59:08.502
There's somethin' else.

704
00:59:08.587 --> 00:59:10.338
All those years I worked
those cow towns.

705
00:59:10.464 --> 00:59:14.217
I was only ever mixed up
in one shootin'. just one.

706
00:59:14.301 --> 00:59:17.720
But a man lost his life. and I took it.

707
00:59:17.804 --> 00:59:20.556
You don't know how that feels. Morg.

708
00:59:20.641 --> 00:59:23.559
Believe me. boy.
you don't ever wanna know.

709
00:59:23.644 --> 00:59:25.603
Not ever.

710
00:59:33.528 --> 00:59:36.280
Didn't even make a dent. did I?

711
00:59:36.365 --> 00:59:38.032
All right.

712
00:59:39.701 --> 00:59:42.578
You're both makin' a big mistake.

713
01:00:00.389 --> 01:00:01.555
Do you wanna ante?

714
01:00:01.640 --> 01:00:03.182
Yeah. fine.

715
01:00:28.709 --> 01:00:31.294
What do you think of the singer?

716
01:00:33.547 --> 01:00:35.047
Nice voice.

717
01:00:36.591 --> 01:00:40.886
Wyatt. Doc won't quit.
He's been at it for 36 hours straight.

718
01:00:41.555 --> 01:00:43.347
Clanton and the McLaury Brothers
came in an hour ago.

719
01:00:43.432 --> 01:00:45.349
I tried to get him to go to bed.
but he won't let go.

720
01:00:45.434 --> 01:00:48.269
I know. and nobody can make him.

721
01:00:52.441 --> 01:00:55.693
Wyatt. just in time. Pull up a chair.

722
01:00:57.446 --> 01:01:01.073
Doc. you been hittin' it
awful hard. haven't ya?

723
01:01:01.158 --> 01:01:05.453
Nonsense.
I've not yet begun to defile myself.

724
01:01:06.288 --> 01:01:07.580
I was wonderin' if maybe you wouldn't

725
01:01:07.664 --> 01:01:08.748
wanna go on over
to the Crystal Palace.

726
01:01:08.874 --> 01:01:11.584
I will not be pawed at.
thank you very much.

727
01:01:11.668 --> 01:01:13.544
-I'm sorry.
-That's right.

728
01:01:13.628 --> 01:01:16.589
Doc can go on day and night.
and then some.

729
01:01:18.550 --> 01:01:22.762
That's my loving man.
Have another one. my loving man.

730
01:01:24.097 --> 01:01:25.681
I'm in.

731
01:01:27.893 --> 01:01:29.226
Hey.

732
01:01:29.311 --> 01:01:32.104
Loving man. you been called.

733
01:01:45.952 --> 01:01:47.495
What is that now?

734
01:01:47.579 --> 01:01:51.957
That 1 2 hands in a row. Holliday?
Son of a bitch. nobody's that lucky.

735
01:01:53.835 --> 01:01:56.796
Why. Ike. whatever do you mean?

736
01:01:58.465 --> 01:02:00.341
Take it easy. boys.

737
01:02:02.719 --> 01:02:05.471
Maybe poker's just not your game. Ike.

738
01:02:07.516 --> 01:02:11.143
I know. let's have a spelling contest.

739
01:02:11.228 --> 01:02:14.021
How 'bout if I just
wring your scrawny neck?

740
01:02:14.106 --> 01:02:15.648
Enough. Ike.

741
01:02:16.817 --> 01:02:19.276
Are you takin' his part?

742
01:02:19.361 --> 01:02:21.987
I'm the one who got cheated!

743
01:02:22.114 --> 01:02:26.826
You goddamn pimps!
You're all in it together.

744
01:02:26.910 --> 01:02:28.285
Nobody's in anything. Ike.

745
01:02:28.370 --> 01:02:30.287
You're drunk.
Go on home and sleep it off.

746
01:02:30.372 --> 01:02:33.040
Get your goddamn hands off me!

747
01:02:33.875 --> 01:02:35.668
Don't you ever put
your hands on me. see?

748
01:02:35.794 --> 01:02:37.586
Don't you ever try to
manhandle a Cowboy.

749
01:02:37.671 --> 01:02:39.422
'cause we'll cut your
goddamn pimp's heart out.

750
01:02:39.506 --> 01:02:40.589
You understand. you pimp?

751
01:02:40.674 --> 01:02:42.633
Don't you threaten me.
you little son of a bitch!

752
01:02:42.717 --> 01:02:45.845
All right! All right!
Come on. easy. Virg. easy!

753
01:02:45.929 --> 01:02:48.556
You just go on home and
forget about it. huh. Ike?

754
01:02:48.682 --> 01:02:50.349
Come on. Virg.

755
01:02:51.393 --> 01:02:53.644
I ain't gonna forget nothin'.

756
01:02:53.728 --> 01:02:57.189
Well. that certainly was a bust.

757
01:02:58.900 --> 01:03:02.445
Come. darlin'. Let's seek
our entertainment elsewhere.

758
01:03:03.780 --> 01:03:06.866
Forget it. Virg. Go on.
Get some fresh air.

759
01:03:19.421 --> 01:03:22.298
-What's wrong. Doc?
-Nothin'. Not a thing.

760
01:03:22.841 --> 01:03:25.009
I'm right as the mail.

761
01:03:28.555 --> 01:03:30.514
Doc? Doc!

762
01:03:31.099 --> 01:03:34.310
All right. get him up.
Let's get him to the hotel.

763
01:03:43.695 --> 01:03:45.988
-What's wrong with him?
-Lunger.

764
01:03:46.072 --> 01:03:48.240
Yeah. well. I hope you die.

765
01:03:49.534 --> 01:03:51.285
Give me my guns.

766
01:03:54.915 --> 01:03:56.081
My rifle.

767
01:03:56.166 --> 01:03:59.335
Goddamn bastards.
Think they can cheat me.

768
01:03:59.419 --> 01:04:02.087
Nobody cheated you. Ike.
Just go home.

769
01:04:03.006 --> 01:04:06.509
I don't take no mouth
from no bartenders. neither.

770
01:04:06.593 --> 01:04:07.885
There. ya see?

771
01:04:07.969 --> 01:04:12.306
Give somebody a rap on the beezer.
get some respect around here.

772
01:04:12.390 --> 01:04:16.685
You tell the Earps. I see 'em
on the street and Doc Holliday.

773
01:04:16.770 --> 01:04:20.439
I'm gonna send them to hell
on a shutter. You tell 'em that.

774
01:04:26.238 --> 01:04:28.280
Pick these guns up.

775
01:04:28.949 --> 01:04:29.949
Come on.

776
01:04:45.549 --> 01:04:47.675
Come on. Ike.

777
01:04:48.301 --> 01:04:49.885
Come on!

778
01:04:52.305 --> 01:04:55.140
-Hey. you walkin'?
-Leave me alone.

779
01:05:01.439 --> 01:05:04.775
-You gonna give Ike back his guns.
-Not till he sobers up.

780
01:05:04.859 --> 01:05:07.570
Wearin' that badge
don't make you right.

781
01:05:07.654 --> 01:05:09.989
Who the hell you think you are?

782
01:05:14.077 --> 01:05:16.078
Watch the way you walk.
you stupid bastard.

783
01:05:16.162 --> 01:05:18.163
Easy. kid. I'm sorry.

784
01:05:19.165 --> 01:05:21.375
I ain't easy and I ain't your kid.

785
01:05:21.501 --> 01:05:24.503
You take your sorry
and shove it up your ass.

786
01:05:27.632 --> 01:05:29.758
I'll fight you right now.

787
01:05:36.516 --> 01:05:38.017
Goddamn it!

788
01:05:38.768 --> 01:05:40.603
You're gonna bleed.

789
01:05:40.687 --> 01:05:43.522
You got a fight comin'. Comin' today.

790
01:05:48.028 --> 01:05:50.154
Bastards! It's comin'!

791
01:05:58.204 --> 01:06:00.706
Your condition's quite advanced.

792
01:06:00.790 --> 01:06:04.585
I'd say you lost some 60%
of your lung tissue. maybe more.

793
01:06:04.669 --> 01:06:06.420
What's the verdict?

794
01:06:06.546 --> 01:06:11.383
Two years. Two days.
Hard to say. If you stop now.

795
01:06:12.886 --> 01:06:16.889
Your smokin'. your drinkin'.
your gamblin'. your nightlife.

796
01:06:17.015 --> 01:06:19.224
You need complete rest.

797
01:06:21.227 --> 01:06:25.189
What I mean is.
you must attempt to deny

798
01:06:25.273 --> 01:06:29.735
-your marital impulse.
-Get out of my sight.

799
01:06:48.588 --> 01:06:51.090
-How are you feeling. Doc?
-Better.

800
01:06:52.050 --> 01:06:54.009
That's good.

801
01:06:54.094 --> 01:06:56.095
I knew it wasn't nothing.

802
01:06:58.598 --> 01:07:00.516
We must talk. darlin'.

803
01:07:02.602 --> 01:07:05.062
It appears

804
01:07:05.146 --> 01:07:08.440
we must redefine the nature
of our association.

805
01:07:14.155 --> 01:07:16.615
I'm a good woman to you. Doc.

806
01:07:17.784 --> 01:07:20.160
Don't I always take care of ya?

807
01:07:20.995 --> 01:07:23.330
Nobody cares for you like me.

808
01:07:24.290 --> 01:07:26.083
I'm a good woman.

809
01:07:27.919 --> 01:07:31.255
Yes. it's true. you are a good woman.

810
01:07:44.728 --> 01:07:46.562
Then again.

811
01:07:47.689 --> 01:07:49.982
you may be the Antichrist.

812
01:08:11.963 --> 01:08:13.380
Goddamn.

813
01:08:14.799 --> 01:08:18.677
Now there's six of 'em.
Hell. this is like a bad dream.

814
01:08:19.637 --> 01:08:22.890
Just stay calm. Use your head.
It'll be all right.

815
01:08:26.478 --> 01:08:28.645
Just the same. though.

816
01:08:30.857 --> 01:08:33.442
guess maybe you better swear me in.

817
01:09:08.311 --> 01:09:12.397
Those Cowboys been telling everybody
in town they're gonna clean you out.

818
01:09:12.524 --> 01:09:15.943
They're back there in that lot
behind the O.K. Corral.

819
01:09:17.237 --> 01:09:19.238
-Thank you. Mayor.
-What're you doin' out of bed. Doc?

820
01:09:19.322 --> 01:09:22.825
What in the hell's goin' on?
Five people come up to my room

821
01:09:22.909 --> 01:09:25.786
tellin' me the Clantons and McLaurys
are gunnin' for us.

822
01:09:25.870 --> 01:09:28.872
We goin' down there or not?
What are we gonna do?

823
01:09:28.957 --> 01:09:30.833
Wait till the liquor wears off.

824
01:09:30.917 --> 01:09:33.502
Soon as they start gettin' headaches.
they'll lose interest.

825
01:09:33.586 --> 01:09:36.129
Lose interest. hell.
They're threatenin' our lives.

826
01:09:36.256 --> 01:09:39.633
-You'll never make that stick.
-They're carryin' guns. Wyatt.

827
01:09:39.717 --> 01:09:41.677
Christ's sake. Virg.
that's a misdemeanor.

828
01:09:41.761 --> 01:09:43.512
You go down there and arrest them.
something goes wrong.

829
01:09:43.596 --> 01:09:46.014
maybe this time somebody really
gets his head broken.

830
01:09:46.099 --> 01:09:47.683
You'll have Cowboys comin' around
lookin' for trouble

831
01:09:47.767 --> 01:09:48.934
from here to Christmas.

832
01:09:49.018 --> 01:09:51.311
You want to risk all that
over a misdemeanor?

833
01:09:51.396 --> 01:09:54.606
Damn right I'll risk it.
They're breakin' the law.

834
01:10:01.072 --> 01:10:04.908
It's not your problem. Doc.
You don't have to mix up in this.

835
01:10:06.703 --> 01:10:09.955
That is a hell of a thing
for you to say to me.

836
01:10:21.467 --> 01:10:23.218
All right. Virg.

837
01:10:25.805 --> 01:10:28.390
Your call. Give Doc the shotgun.

838
01:10:30.268 --> 01:10:34.438
They'll be less apt to get nervy
if he's on the street howitzer.

839
01:11:19.901 --> 01:11:21.610
Go on! Get home!

840
01:11:23.613 --> 01:11:25.364
Goddamn kid.

841
01:11:37.251 --> 01:11:40.295
How the hell did we
get ourselves into this?

842
01:11:43.633 --> 01:11:45.092
You don't have to worry about a thing.

843
01:11:45.176 --> 01:11:46.426
I just went over there
and disarmed them.

844
01:11:46.511 --> 01:11:49.554
You did? Come on. boys.

845
01:11:49.639 --> 01:11:52.891
Gentlemen. I'm not
gonna allow any trouble.

846
01:12:15.707 --> 01:12:18.750
We're here to disarm you.
Throw up your hands.

847
01:12:23.131 --> 01:12:25.674
Hold it! That's not what I want!

848
01:13:00.168 --> 01:13:02.127
Oh. my God.

849
01:13:11.471 --> 01:13:13.472
Billy! Billy!

850
01:13:20.104 --> 01:13:22.522
Stop! No! No!

851
01:13:23.232 --> 01:13:25.734
Don't shoot! I got no gun!

852
01:13:25.818 --> 01:13:28.070
Please don't shoot me! I got no gun!

853
01:13:28.154 --> 01:13:31.490
This fight's commenced!
Get to fightin' or get away!

854
01:13:33.493 --> 01:13:35.410
-That's it!
-Shut the door!

855
01:13:50.885 --> 01:13:53.261
Give me your goddamned gun!
Damn it!

856
01:13:53.346 --> 01:13:55.597
Billy! Billy!

857
01:13:55.681 --> 01:13:57.516
Doc. behind us!

858
01:14:24.710 --> 01:14:27.254
I got you now. you son of a bitch.

859
01:14:27.338 --> 01:14:29.422
You're a daisy if you do.

860
01:14:43.813 --> 01:14:46.356
Morgan. hold quiet now.

861
01:14:57.410 --> 01:14:59.536
Here you go. Easy. Easy. man.

862
01:14:59.620 --> 01:15:02.372
-I got you. All right.
-All right!

863
01:15:04.959 --> 01:15:07.169
All of you are under arrest.

864
01:15:17.638 --> 01:15:20.974
I don't think I'll let you
arrest us today. Behan.

865
01:15:50.171 --> 01:15:52.172
Virg!

866
01:15:52.256 --> 01:15:54.049
Virgil!

867
01:16:14.779 --> 01:16:18.198
Well. I guess we did
our good deed for today. Mayor.

868
01:17:42.867 --> 01:17:45.910
You were right.
It's nothin' like I thought.

869
01:17:47.747 --> 01:17:50.457
-I almost wish that...
-I know. Morgan.

870
01:17:51.792 --> 01:17:53.918
I know. Me too.

871
01:18:05.931 --> 01:18:08.058
Outta the way!

872
01:18:12.688 --> 01:18:14.272
Gettin' warmer.

873
01:18:15.232 --> 01:18:17.275
Guess spring's comin'.

874
01:18:17.360 --> 01:18:19.611
Hello. Billy. I say hello.

875
01:18:19.695 --> 01:18:21.863
It's deputy!
And I don't want to talk to you!

876
01:18:21.947 --> 01:18:24.699
Those men you killed were my friends.

877
01:18:25.785 --> 01:18:28.161
I'm just a nothin'.
But if I wasn't. I'd fight you right now.

878
01:18:28.245 --> 01:18:30.622
so I don't want to talk to you.

879
01:18:32.792 --> 01:18:35.293
All they ever did was laugh at him.

880
01:18:44.053 --> 01:18:47.222
Sister boy should've stuck around.

881
01:18:49.850 --> 01:18:53.561
-What do you want. Ringo?
-I want your blood.

882
01:18:55.189 --> 01:18:57.399
And I want your souls.

883
01:18:57.983 --> 01:19:00.360
And I want 'em both right now.

884
01:19:00.444 --> 01:19:03.947
-I don't want any more trouble.
-Well. ya got trouble!

885
01:19:06.283 --> 01:19:08.493
And it starts with you.

886
01:19:12.331 --> 01:19:14.874
I'm not gonna fight you. Ringo.

887
01:19:15.835 --> 01:19:17.836
There's no money in it.

888
01:19:18.462 --> 01:19:20.505
Sober up. Come on. boys.

889
01:19:21.006 --> 01:19:23.508
You wretched slugs.

890
01:19:23.592 --> 01:19:26.010
Don't any of ya have the guts
to play for blood?

891
01:19:26.095 --> 01:19:28.179
I'm your huckleberry.

892
01:19:30.141 --> 01:19:32.100
That's just my game.

893
01:19:39.650 --> 01:19:43.361
All right. lunger. You go to hell.

894
01:19:45.030 --> 01:19:48.032
-I'll put you out of your misery.
-Say when.

895
01:19:48.868 --> 01:19:51.411
-Johnny. don't!
-No. Johnny!

896
01:19:52.955 --> 01:19:54.622
-Get off!
-Easy now!

897
01:19:54.707 --> 01:19:56.249
-Get off!
-It ain't nothin'.

898
01:19:56.333 --> 01:19:59.210
Don't mind him!
He's just drunk. that's all.

899
01:20:02.214 --> 01:20:03.840
Cool down. Johnny!

900
01:20:03.924 --> 01:20:06.134
No! No!

901
01:20:07.136 --> 01:20:09.345
I want them spittin' blood!

902
01:20:09.430 --> 01:20:11.931
Easy. son. easy! Now ain't the time!

903
01:20:12.016 --> 01:20:13.683
Slow down. Ringo.

904
01:20:16.061 --> 01:20:17.896
I tell ya. boys. even I'm worried
what's gonna happen

905
01:20:18.022 --> 01:20:19.522
once Ringo runs this outfit.

906
01:20:19.607 --> 01:20:22.358
God have mercy!

907
01:20:22.443 --> 01:20:25.487
-Juanito. their time will come.
-Gentlemen.

908
01:20:26.280 --> 01:20:28.948
-Let's go get bullied. boy!
-Let's go get soused!

909
01:20:29.074 --> 01:20:31.117
-Barber.
-Yes. sir?

910
01:20:34.205 --> 01:20:35.747
Proceed. sir.

911
01:20:52.223 --> 01:20:55.642
Listen to me. I need to speak with you.

912
01:20:56.435 --> 01:20:58.144
Not now. I'm busy.

913
01:20:59.688 --> 01:21:02.232
I see what's going on
between you and Wyatt.

914
01:21:02.316 --> 01:21:04.984
I'm not a fool. But listen to me.

915
01:21:06.111 --> 01:21:08.780
Lots of so-called hard cases
and tough nuts

916
01:21:08.906 --> 01:21:10.281
come and go around this town.

917
01:21:10.366 --> 01:21:14.577
but none of them has a clue
about the real play. none of them.

918
01:21:14.662 --> 01:21:18.623
Now after tonight. there'll be one man
in charge of Tombstone.

919
01:21:18.707 --> 01:21:21.501
You'll be happy to know him. Bet on it.

920
01:21:31.470 --> 01:21:33.763
Gonna be one of those nights.

921
01:21:36.934 --> 01:21:39.602
It's gettin' late. boys.
I'm gonna go to bed.

922
01:21:39.687 --> 01:21:42.355
-Good night. Virg.
-Good night. Morg.

923
01:21:43.941 --> 01:21:47.026
Bundle up. Virg.
It's gettin' cold out there.

924
01:21:47.152 --> 01:21:48.278
Yeah.

925
01:22:15.556 --> 01:22:17.515
Tower of Babel.

926
01:22:18.267 --> 01:22:20.685
Death and the Devil.

927
01:22:20.769 --> 01:22:21.769
Oh. dear.

928
01:22:21.854 --> 01:22:24.689
Oh. Allie. I wish you'd learn to play
a real card game.

929
01:22:29.528 --> 01:22:32.363
-More tea. Mattie?
-No. no.

930
01:22:32.448 --> 01:22:34.365
-Are you all right. Mattie?
-Yes.

931
01:22:34.450 --> 01:22:37.118
-Are you expecting someone?
-Only Virg.

932
01:22:42.333 --> 01:22:46.044
Please. I know it's awful
to come here. but listen.

933
01:22:46.128 --> 01:22:48.921
I think something's
gonna happen tonight.

934
01:22:51.050 --> 01:22:53.259
It's Virg.

935
01:22:53.385 --> 01:22:55.053
No! Get down!

936
01:23:13.697 --> 01:23:16.199
That thunder's sure gettin' close.

937
01:23:28.253 --> 01:23:31.214
Virgil. What'd ya forget?

938
01:23:42.267 --> 01:23:43.768
Wyatt.

939
01:23:56.782 --> 01:23:59.742
Will you hurry with that water. please?

940
01:23:59.827 --> 01:24:01.994
Come on. Lou.

941
01:24:05.457 --> 01:24:07.417
Wyatt! Wyatt!

942
01:24:10.295 --> 01:24:12.213
They hit Clum's house too.
shot up his wife.

943
01:24:12.297 --> 01:24:14.465
His wife! Whoever heard of that?

944
01:24:14.550 --> 01:24:17.719
They're bugs. Wyatt. All that
smart talk about live and let live.

945
01:24:17.803 --> 01:24:19.387
There ain't no live
and let live with bugs.

946
01:24:19.471 --> 01:24:22.140
All right. you listen to me now.
We gotta get out of here.

947
01:24:22.224 --> 01:24:25.518
Get out of here?
Listen to yourself. Wyatt.

948
01:24:25.602 --> 01:24:28.187
Lie down and crawl or you might
get hurt? What kind of talk is that?

949
01:24:28.272 --> 01:24:30.481
-Do you see what's happening here?
-What?

950
01:24:30.607 --> 01:24:33.568
What do you mean?
What are you saying?

951
01:24:33.652 --> 01:24:35.486
No. Please. no.

952
01:24:35.571 --> 01:24:39.449
I'm afraid your husband's
going to lose the use of his arm.

953
01:24:39.533 --> 01:24:41.617
Oh. God. no.

954
01:24:43.662 --> 01:24:45.705
Don't worry. Allie girl.

955
01:24:45.789 --> 01:24:48.666
I still got one good arm
to hold you with.

956
01:24:50.919 --> 01:24:51.919
Goddamn!

957
01:24:52.004 --> 01:24:56.591
-Goddamn sons of bitches!
-Morgan. wait a minute! Virg.

958
01:24:56.675 --> 01:24:59.552
-You had to be so damn smart.
-I'm sorry. Allie.

959
01:24:59.636 --> 01:25:01.179
I told you. Virg.

960
01:25:01.263 --> 01:25:03.806
-Not now. Wyatt.
-All right.

961
01:25:03.891 --> 01:25:05.933
All right. what do you want me to do?

962
01:25:06.018 --> 01:25:09.854
-Just leave me alone. for God's sakes.
-Virg...

963
01:25:09.938 --> 01:25:12.690
He doesn't want to talk now. Wyatt!

964
01:25:29.875 --> 01:25:32.877
I heard about what they did
to your women. That was wrong.

965
01:25:32.961 --> 01:25:37.131
I'm here to let you know that it
wasn't me. I had no part of it.

966
01:25:37.216 --> 01:25:41.636
No? Brothers to the bone.
right. McMasters?

967
01:25:41.720 --> 01:25:45.431
No. Not anymore. Not after this night.

968
01:25:46.725 --> 01:25:50.561
He's right. Wyatt. You want us
for anything. we're with you.

969
01:25:50.687 --> 01:25:52.063
Come on.

970
01:26:55.711 --> 01:26:57.712
Hold him!

971
01:26:59.298 --> 01:27:01.757
No! Get her out of here! Jesus!

972
01:27:03.135 --> 01:27:05.636
Somebody shut that dog up!

973
01:27:09.474 --> 01:27:11.350
I said hold him. goddamn it!

974
01:27:11.435 --> 01:27:14.812
Somebody get
that goddamn dog out of here!

975
01:27:14.897 --> 01:27:17.481
The bullet's too deep. I can't get it out.

976
01:27:20.235 --> 01:27:23.029
The way it's lodged in there. I'm sorry.

977
01:27:23.113 --> 01:27:25.489
Easy. Morg. Is that better?

978
01:27:26.909 --> 01:27:28.159
Yeah.

979
01:27:31.413 --> 01:27:35.124
You were right. Wyatt.
They got me good.

980
01:27:37.920 --> 01:27:41.130
Don't let 'em get you. brother.
You're the one.

981
01:27:42.549 --> 01:27:44.008
Easy. Morg.

982
01:27:45.844 --> 01:27:47.970
Don't worry about that now.

983
01:27:52.851 --> 01:27:56.145
Remember what I said
about seein' a light when you're dyin'?

984
01:27:56.772 --> 01:27:59.023
Yeah. Yeah.

985
01:27:59.775 --> 01:28:01.776
That ain't true.

986
01:28:01.860 --> 01:28:04.153
I can't see a damn thing.

987
01:28:07.908 --> 01:28:09.158
Morg?

988
01:28:14.039 --> 01:28:15.289
Morg!

989
01:28:21.630 --> 01:28:23.047
Morg?

990
01:28:37.688 --> 01:28:39.063
No.

991
01:28:41.817 --> 01:28:43.776
Morgan! No!

992
01:28:43.860 --> 01:28:47.613
Morgan. don't die! I love you!

993
01:28:47.698 --> 01:28:49.782
Don't die!

994
01:29:02.504 --> 01:29:05.589
Why? Why him?

995
01:29:09.302 --> 01:29:13.556
-No. No. get away from me!
-Wyatt!

996
01:29:14.433 --> 01:29:17.309
Can't you see? Get away from me!

997
01:29:52.763 --> 01:29:54.388
Morgan!

998
01:30:46.274 --> 01:30:49.193
And so she walked
out of our lives forever.

999
01:31:25.063 --> 01:31:27.398
I want you to know it's over.

1000
01:31:29.568 --> 01:31:30.901
Well.

1001
01:31:33.071 --> 01:31:34.405
Bye.

1002
01:31:36.408 --> 01:31:38.367
You smell that. Bill?

1003
01:31:40.579 --> 01:31:42.746
Smells like someone died.

1004
01:31:44.499 --> 01:31:46.208
Jesus. Johnny.

1005
01:32:09.858 --> 01:32:11.233
Ike.

1006
01:32:12.903 --> 01:32:17.156
Take Stillwell and finish it.

1007
01:32:32.172 --> 01:32:34.590
Now. you take care of yourself.

1008
01:32:35.800 --> 01:32:38.969
-That's Virgil with the women.
-He's mine!

1009
01:32:39.095 --> 01:32:42.723
-All aboard!
-Hey. Mattie! Where's Wyatt?

1010
01:32:42.807 --> 01:32:45.017
Right behind you. Stillwell.

1011
01:32:46.394 --> 01:32:47.811
No!

1012
01:33:02.452 --> 01:33:04.411
Sweet Jesus. Don't shoot.

1013
01:33:22.847 --> 01:33:24.974
All right. Clanton.

1014
01:33:25.058 --> 01:33:28.477
You called down the thunder.
Well. now you got it.

1015
01:33:31.064 --> 01:33:34.525
You see that?
It says "United States Marshal."

1016
01:33:34.609 --> 01:33:37.444
Wyatt. Please don't kill me. Please.

1017
01:33:37.529 --> 01:33:41.782
Take a good look at him. Ike.
'cause that's how you're gonna end up.

1018
01:33:43.493 --> 01:33:46.537
The Cowboys are finished.
You understand me?

1019
01:33:46.621 --> 01:33:50.124
I see a red sash.
I kill the man wearin' it.

1020
01:33:50.208 --> 01:33:52.209
So run. you cur.

1021
01:33:53.044 --> 01:33:57.047
Run! Tell all the other curs
the law is comin'!

1022
01:33:58.508 --> 01:34:00.384
You tell 'em I'm comin'!

1023
01:34:00.468 --> 01:34:03.429
And Hell's comin' with me. you hear?

1024
01:34:03.513 --> 01:34:05.556
Hell's comin' with me!

1025
01:34:39.424 --> 01:34:41.258
Nobody move!

1026
01:34:41.343 --> 01:34:43.969
Nonsense. By all means. move.

1027
01:36:00.296 --> 01:36:01.839
Get down!

1028
01:36:13.977 --> 01:36:15.644
Hey. Wyatt!

1029
01:36:15.728 --> 01:36:17.855
How the hell are ya?

1030
01:36:30.118 --> 01:36:32.494
I got some boys over there behind ya!

1031
01:36:32.579 --> 01:36:35.914
Got you in a little crossfire.
How do ya like that?

1032
01:36:38.251 --> 01:36:41.211
Come on!
Think of something fast. would ya?

1033
01:36:43.840 --> 01:36:47.259
Wyatt? Hey. Wyatt.

1034
01:36:48.052 --> 01:36:49.928
-No.
-Wyatt!

1035
01:36:51.931 --> 01:36:54.308
-No.
-Wyatt. what are you doin'?

1036
01:36:55.268 --> 01:36:56.727
Look at that.

1037
01:36:57.395 --> 01:36:58.770
Yeah.

1038
01:36:59.731 --> 01:37:02.107
Come and get some. boy.

1039
01:37:06.779 --> 01:37:08.864
No! Let me!

1040
01:37:16.289 --> 01:37:17.706
No.

1041
01:37:17.916 --> 01:37:21.710
-Son of a bitch.
-No!

1042
01:37:26.633 --> 01:37:28.467
Jesus Christ!

1043
01:37:39.103 --> 01:37:41.813
No. No!

1044
01:37:53.785 --> 01:37:56.495
Did you ever see anything
like that before?

1045
01:37:56.579 --> 01:37:58.956
Hell. I ain't never even
heard of anything like that.

1046
01:37:59.040 --> 01:38:00.374
Nothin'.

1047
01:38:01.292 --> 01:38:02.876
Where is he?

1048
01:38:05.255 --> 01:38:07.214
Down by the creek.

1049
01:38:07.298 --> 01:38:09.174
walkin' on water.

1050
01:38:09.259 --> 01:38:12.511
Well. let's hope he's got
another miracle up his sleeve.

1051
01:38:12.637 --> 01:38:16.223
'Cause if I know Ringo.
he's headed straight for us.

1052
01:38:17.767 --> 01:38:21.311
Well. if they were my brothers.
I'd want revenge too.

1053
01:38:21.396 --> 01:38:23.397
No. Make no mistake.

1054
01:38:24.983 --> 01:38:27.317
It's not revenge he's after.

1055
01:38:28.820 --> 01:38:30.779
It's a reckoning.

1056
01:38:41.207 --> 01:38:45.669
Doc. You ought to be in bed. What
the hell you doin' this for anyway?

1057
01:38:46.504 --> 01:38:48.505
Wyatt Earp is my friend.

1058
01:38:49.841 --> 01:38:52.175
Hell. I got lots of friends.

1059
01:38:53.720 --> 01:38:55.137
I don't.

1060
01:39:14.991 --> 01:39:16.533
My God.

1061
01:39:19.621 --> 01:39:22.289
-Are you all right?
-What do you care?

1062
01:39:23.249 --> 01:39:25.584
It was your friends that did it.

1063
01:39:27.211 --> 01:39:31.048
Must've been Claiborne and Fuller.
They left here last night.

1064
01:39:32.050 --> 01:39:33.842
Oh. no.

1065
01:39:33.926 --> 01:39:36.553
They tried to take my watch.

1066
01:39:36.638 --> 01:39:39.723
He cursed them for cowards.
and they shot him.

1067
01:39:41.309 --> 01:39:43.852
I don't understand any of this.

1068
01:39:45.480 --> 01:39:47.481
I just know it's ugly.

1069
01:39:48.107 --> 01:39:49.900
You're all ugly.

1070
01:39:50.652 --> 01:39:52.819
and he was beautiful.

1071
01:39:53.905 --> 01:39:58.909
He tried to bring something fine into
your ugly world. and you shot him for it.

1072
01:40:03.039 --> 01:40:05.082
Not that you care.

1073
01:40:16.511 --> 01:40:19.471
-Billy. Where you goin'?
-I'm not goin' with you.

1074
01:40:19.555 --> 01:40:21.848
Billy! Billy. get back here!

1075
01:40:21.933 --> 01:40:24.434
I'm sorry. sir.
but we got to have some law.

1076
01:40:24.519 --> 01:40:27.479
-Billy!
-Let him go. Who cares?

1077
01:40:28.606 --> 01:40:31.566
Get on out!
Get the hell outta here! Go on!

1078
01:40:32.318 --> 01:40:34.736
Party's over. boys. Let's go!

1079
01:40:50.002 --> 01:40:51.253
Halt.

1080
01:40:57.802 --> 01:41:00.512
Ringo and Behan are out in front.

1081
01:41:00.596 --> 01:41:03.473
There is about 30 of 'em.

1082
01:41:05.810 --> 01:41:07.978
They're all wearin' badges.

1083
01:41:09.480 --> 01:41:10.981
Christ.

1084
01:41:11.983 --> 01:41:14.484
We gotta find a place to hole up.

1085
01:41:16.070 --> 01:41:17.320
Doc.

1086
01:41:18.072 --> 01:41:19.990
Grab him.

1087
01:41:22.368 --> 01:41:23.702
I got him.

1088
01:41:24.954 --> 01:41:26.496
I got him!

1089
01:41:32.712 --> 01:41:34.379
Is this Henry Hooker's ranch?

1090
01:41:34.505 --> 01:41:37.340
That's right. And I'm Hooker.

1091
01:41:37.425 --> 01:41:39.676
We got a sick man.

1092
01:41:39.761 --> 01:41:42.012
And our horses are done in.

1093
01:41:42.096 --> 01:41:45.682
Put him up at my place.
as long as it's just tonight.

1094
01:41:46.726 --> 01:41:48.518
We're in debt to you.

1095
01:41:56.861 --> 01:41:58.862
I know you boys
have got to keep movin'.

1096
01:41:58.946 --> 01:42:01.281
but he looks pretty bad to me.

1097
01:42:29.227 --> 01:42:32.103
They got held up.
and their boss actor got killed.

1098
01:42:32.230 --> 01:42:35.899
They came here to water the horses.
then they'll push on.

1099
01:42:52.750 --> 01:42:56.711
I'm sorry about your friend.
And I'm sorry that I...

1100
01:42:57.171 --> 01:42:59.798
I forgave you the moment you said it.

1101
01:42:59.882 --> 01:43:02.592
You did? Well...

1102
01:43:04.804 --> 01:43:06.137
Thank you.

1103
01:43:07.598 --> 01:43:09.182
All set.

1104
01:43:11.602 --> 01:43:13.144
I have to go.

1105
01:43:16.482 --> 01:43:17.941
Wait.

1106
01:44:04.572 --> 01:44:06.489
What the hell is that?

1107
01:44:26.677 --> 01:44:28.511
They got McMasters!

1108
01:44:31.807 --> 01:44:35.560
Ringo wanted to make sure
he got your attention. Marshal!

1109
01:44:35.645 --> 01:44:37.604
He wants a straight-up fight.
just you and him.

1110
01:44:37.688 --> 01:44:39.940
to settle this thing once and for all.

1111
01:44:40.024 --> 01:44:43.568
Oak grove at the mouth
of Silver Springs Canyon. 7:00!

1112
01:44:43.653 --> 01:44:46.279
You tell him I'll be there!

1113
01:44:46.364 --> 01:44:48.823
-Are you crazy?
-I'll be there!

1114
01:44:50.910 --> 01:44:52.494
It's not finished.

1115
01:45:08.010 --> 01:45:11.429
After I'm done with Wyatt Earp.

1116
01:45:11.555 --> 01:45:15.475
take your Cowboys and finish off
Creek Johnson and Texas Jack.

1117
01:45:17.395 --> 01:45:19.396
You burn 'em. Ike.

1118
01:45:21.857 --> 01:45:23.066
Burn 'em all.

1119
01:45:23.150 --> 01:45:25.944
Hell. Johnny.
he ain't even gonna show.

1120
01:45:28.781 --> 01:45:30.281
He'll show.

1121
01:45:33.577 --> 01:45:37.622
I spent my whole life not knowin'
what I wanted outta life.

1122
01:45:38.165 --> 01:45:40.208
just chasin' my tail.

1123
01:45:40.626 --> 01:45:44.170
Now for the first time
I know exactly what I want.

1124
01:45:44.255 --> 01:45:45.630
and who.

1125
01:45:47.967 --> 01:45:50.844
And that's the damnable misery of it.

1126
01:45:56.350 --> 01:45:58.059
What makes a man like Ringo. Doc?

1127
01:45:58.144 --> 01:46:01.146
What makes him
do the things he does?

1128
01:46:01.272 --> 01:46:03.273
A man like Ringo

1129
01:46:04.442 --> 01:46:08.278
got a great empty hole
right through the middle of him.

1130
01:46:10.281 --> 01:46:14.534
He can never kill enough
or steal enough

1131
01:46:14.618 --> 01:46:17.454
or inflict enough pain to ever fill it.

1132
01:46:18.330 --> 01:46:20.290
What does he need?

1133
01:46:21.542 --> 01:46:23.460
Revenge.

1134
01:46:26.881 --> 01:46:28.298
For what?

1135
01:46:34.430 --> 01:46:35.847
Bein' born.

1136
01:46:50.529 --> 01:46:52.280
It all happened so fast with Curly Bill

1137
01:46:52.364 --> 01:46:53.740
I didn't really have time
to think about it.

1138
01:46:53.824 --> 01:46:57.118
but I've had plenty of time
to think about this.

1139
01:47:04.001 --> 01:47:06.252
I can't beat him. can I?

1140
01:47:07.963 --> 01:47:09.172
No.

1141
01:47:16.597 --> 01:47:19.557
Wait. I'm goin' with ya.

1142
01:47:26.065 --> 01:47:29.484
Oh. God. I'm sorry.

1143
01:47:30.402 --> 01:47:32.570
I'm sorry. Wyatt.

1144
01:47:32.655 --> 01:47:34.823
It's all right. Doc.

1145
01:47:38.536 --> 01:47:41.121
What's it like to wear one of those?

1146
01:48:08.482 --> 01:48:09.983
Don't worry.

1147
01:48:10.067 --> 01:48:13.278
They want him.
they gotta come over us first.

1148
01:48:40.431 --> 01:48:44.559
He's waitin' for you by the big oak.
quarter mile up that trail.

1149
01:48:50.441 --> 01:48:53.276
They're not givin' ya any safe-conduct.

1150
01:48:53.986 --> 01:48:58.031
Shootin' starts. you better kick east
to the New Mexico line.

1151
01:49:00.743 --> 01:49:02.785
I ain't got the words.

1152
01:49:02.912 --> 01:49:04.787
I know.

1153
01:49:05.456 --> 01:49:06.956
Me neither.

1154
01:49:15.633 --> 01:49:17.217
Well.

1155
01:49:23.849 --> 01:49:26.392
I didn't think ya had it in you.

1156
01:49:26.477 --> 01:49:28.561
I'm your huckleberry.

1157
01:49:32.233 --> 01:49:34.734
Why. Johnny Ringo.

1158
01:49:35.569 --> 01:49:38.947
you look like somebody
just walked over your grave.

1159
01:49:40.824 --> 01:49:43.117
Fight's not with you. Holliday.

1160
01:49:43.202 --> 01:49:47.872
I'll beg to differ. sir. We started
a game we never got to finish.

1161
01:49:48.999 --> 01:49:51.417
Play for blood. remember?

1162
01:49:53.629 --> 01:49:55.672
I was just foolin' about.

1163
01:49:57.758 --> 01:49:59.384
I wasn't.

1164
01:50:00.928 --> 01:50:03.137
And this time

1165
01:50:04.181 --> 01:50:05.723
it's legal.

1166
01:50:14.233 --> 01:50:17.402
All right. lunger. Let's do it.

1167
01:50:52.021 --> 01:50:53.479
Say when.

1168
01:51:12.291 --> 01:51:14.834
Come on. Come on!

1169
01:51:15.836 --> 01:51:17.628
Oh. Johnny. Come on!

1170
01:51:23.844 --> 01:51:26.929
You're no daisy. You're no daisy at all!

1171
01:51:28.599 --> 01:51:30.099
Poor soul.

1172
01:51:31.435 --> 01:51:33.853
You were just too high-strung.

1173
01:51:44.531 --> 01:51:47.992
I'm afraid the strain
was more than he could bear.

1174
01:51:55.876 --> 01:51:59.295
Oh. I wasn't quite
as sick as I made out.

1175
01:52:03.675 --> 01:52:05.259
Good God.

1176
01:52:11.975 --> 01:52:13.976
My hypocrisy goes only so far.

1177
01:52:19.733 --> 01:52:21.150
All right.

1178
01:52:22.444 --> 01:52:23.736
Let's finish it.

1179
01:52:23.821 --> 01:52:28.408
Indeed. sir. The last charge
of Wyatt Earp and his immortals.

1180
01:53:21.545 --> 01:53:23.671
Come on! Get going!

1181
01:53:28.760 --> 01:53:30.428
Look at this!

1182
01:54:51.969 --> 01:54:53.553
Hello. Wyatt.

1183
01:54:54.137 --> 01:54:56.514
Father Feeney and I were just

1184
01:54:57.432 --> 01:55:01.269
investigating the mysteries
of the Church of Rome.

1185
01:55:03.146 --> 01:55:08.109
It appears my hypocrisy
knows no bounds.

1186
01:55:08.986 --> 01:55:12.697
You're no hypocrite. Doc.
You just like to sound like one.

1187
01:55:13.407 --> 01:55:15.658
I brought you somethin'.

1188
01:55:21.665 --> 01:55:25.334
Well. let's see. Where are we today?

1189
01:55:25.460 --> 01:55:28.421
I'm $17 down to you.

1190
01:55:28.505 --> 01:55:32.425
-Two bits a hand. Stud?
-You keep comin' back here.

1191
01:55:32.509 --> 01:55:35.511
I told you not to. and I meant it.

1192
01:55:35.596 --> 01:55:39.181
You're the only person
I can afford to lose to anymore.

1193
01:55:41.435 --> 01:55:43.603
How we feelin' today. Doc?

1194
01:55:44.980 --> 01:55:47.064
I'm dying. How are you?

1195
01:55:48.025 --> 01:55:49.900
Pretty much the same.

1196
01:55:50.652 --> 01:55:53.279
So now we add self-pity
to your list of frailties.

1197
01:55:53.363 --> 01:55:54.947
All right. Doc.

1198
01:55:55.032 --> 01:55:57.700
All right. how many cards you want?

1199
01:55:58.368 --> 01:56:00.703
I don't want to play anymore.

1200
01:56:02.372 --> 01:56:04.123
How many?

1201
01:56:04.625 --> 01:56:08.044
Damn you. You're the most fallible.

1202
01:56:09.963 --> 01:56:12.632
stubborn. self-deluded.

1203
01:56:12.716 --> 01:56:15.051
bull-headed man
I've ever known in my entire life.

1204
01:56:15.177 --> 01:56:16.510
I call.

1205
01:56:17.304 --> 01:56:19.263
-You win.
-Yet withal.

1206
01:56:19.806 --> 01:56:24.352
you're the only human being in my
entire life who ever gave me hope.

1207
01:56:30.901 --> 01:56:33.569
I was in love once.

1208
01:56:35.572 --> 01:56:37.323
My first cousin.

1209
01:56:37.949 --> 01:56:40.409
She was 1 5.

1210
01:56:43.580 --> 01:56:45.289
We were both so...

1211
01:56:46.708 --> 01:56:48.709
That's good. Doc.

1212
01:56:49.503 --> 01:56:51.712
That's good. What happened?

1213
01:56:55.258 --> 01:56:58.260
She joined a convent over the affair.

1214
01:56:59.096 --> 01:57:01.472
She was all I ever wanted.

1215
01:57:03.975 --> 01:57:06.102
What did you want?

1216
01:57:06.728 --> 01:57:08.979
Just to live a normal life.

1217
01:57:09.773 --> 01:57:13.275
There's no normal life. Wyatt.
There's just life.

1218
01:57:14.653 --> 01:57:16.654
Now get on with it.

1219
01:57:17.572 --> 01:57:19.115
Don't know how.

1220
01:57:21.493 --> 01:57:24.328
Sure you do. Say goodbye to me.

1221
01:57:26.331 --> 01:57:28.791
Go grab that spirited actress

1222
01:57:28.875 --> 01:57:30.751
and make her your own.

1223
01:57:32.170 --> 01:57:35.506
Take that beauty and run.
and don't look back.

1224
01:57:35.590 --> 01:57:39.385
Live every second.
Live right up to the hilt.

1225
01:57:40.303 --> 01:57:42.221
Live. Wyatt.

1226
01:57:43.140 --> 01:57:44.807
Live for me.

1227
01:57:46.643 --> 01:57:49.478
Wyatt. if you ever were my friend.

1228
01:57:49.563 --> 01:57:52.982
if you ever had even
the slightest feelin' for me.

1229
01:57:53.066 --> 01:57:54.608
leave now.

1230
01:57:55.193 --> 01:57:56.694
Leave now.

1231
01:58:01.575 --> 01:58:03.075
Please?

1232
01:58:15.255 --> 01:58:17.840
Thanks for always bein' there. Doc.

1233
01:58:46.036 --> 01:58:47.787
I'll be damned.

1234
01:58:50.540 --> 01:58:52.208
This is funny.

1235
01:59:12.813 --> 01:59:15.397
I never thought I would see
Gilbert and Sullivan performed

1236
01:59:15.482 --> 01:59:17.399
right here in Denver.

1237
01:59:18.735 --> 01:59:21.070
-Good night. Josie.
-Good night.

1238
01:59:21.863 --> 01:59:23.405
Good show.

1239
01:59:40.257 --> 01:59:43.342
Ya ever see the sun come up
over the Rockies?

1240
01:59:43.927 --> 01:59:47.471
It hits all of a sudden.
and below there's California.

1241
01:59:48.682 --> 01:59:51.433
And you swear
you're lookin' at heaven.

1242
01:59:59.276 --> 02:00:01.652
I have nothing left.

1243
02:00:01.778 --> 02:00:03.946
nothing to give you.

1244
02:00:04.906 --> 02:00:08.242
I have no pride. no dignity.

1245
02:00:09.494 --> 02:00:13.289
No money. I don't even know
how we'll make a living. but...

1246
02:00:18.295 --> 02:00:21.297
I promise I'll love you
the rest of your life.

1247
02:00:36.313 --> 02:00:39.982
Don't worry. Wyatt. My family's rich.

1248
02:00:47.365 --> 02:00:49.867
What shall we do first?

1249
02:00:49.951 --> 02:00:53.120
What you wanted to do
the first night we met.

1250
02:00:53.204 --> 02:00:54.580
Remember?

1251
02:00:57.542 --> 02:00:59.752
May I have this dance?

1252
02:01:01.838 --> 02:01:05.299
-Yes.
-And then we'll have room service.

1253
02:01:12.682 --> 02:01:16.226
The power of the Cowboy Gang
was broken forever.

1254
02:01:16.311 --> 02:01:18.812
lke Clanton was shot and killed
two years later

1255
02:01:18.897 --> 02:01:21.106
during an attempted robbery.

1256
02:01:21.191 --> 02:01:25.778
Mattie died of a drug overdose
shortly after she left Tombstone.

1257
02:01:25.862 --> 02:01:29.031
Virgil and Allie Earp
moved to California. where Virgil.

1258
02:01:29.157 --> 02:01:32.743
despite the use of only one arm.
became a town sheriff.

1259
02:01:33.161 --> 02:01:36.789
Wyatt and Josephine
embarked on a series of adventures.

1260
02:01:36.873 --> 02:01:42.336
Up or down. thin or flush. in 47 years
they never left each other's side.

1261
02:01:42.420 --> 02:01:45.714
Wyatt Earp died
in Los Angeles in 1929.

1262
02:01:46.383 --> 02:01:48.384
Among the pallbearers at his funeral

1263
02:01:48.468 --> 02:01:52.346
were early Western movie stars
William S. Hart and Tom Mix.

1264
02:01:53.139 --> 02:01:54.807
Tom Mix wept.

